3
00:01:14,087 --> 00:01:16,222
(SHARP BREATHS)

4
00:01:16,589 --> 00:01:21,594
WOMAN: <i>* Having been eye
And ear witnesses ♪</i>

5
00:01:26,632 --> 00:01:30,636
<i>♪ To all that our Mother
Has done ♪</i>

6
00:01:34,274 --> 00:01:39,680
<i>♪ From the first time
She opened the Gospel ♪</i>

7
00:01:43,183 --> 00:01:48,021
<i>♪ Till she sung
Her final song ♪</i>

8
00:01:55,862 --> 00:02:01,067
<i>♪ It seems only good
To answer ♪</i>

9
00:02:05,239 --> 00:02:10,477
<i>♪ The request
Of our brethren and sisters ♪</i>

10
00:02:13,114 --> 00:02:17,151
<i>♪ Make a faithful record ♪</i>

11
00:02:17,251 --> 00:02:21,088
<i>♪ Of Mother Ann Lee ♪</i>

12
00:02:23,190 --> 00:02:28,362
<i>♪ The woman
Clothed by the sun ♪</i>

13
00:02:32,299 --> 00:02:37,071
<i>♪ The woman
Clothed by the sun ♪</i>

14
00:02:42,343 --> 00:02:47,382
<i>♪ The woman
Clothed by the sun ♪</i>

15
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:10,238
As one might expect
of a miraculous person,

16
00:03:11,573 --> 00:03:17,045
Ann Lee was born
on the 29th of February

17
00:03:18,480 --> 00:03:22,017
in the year 1736.

18
00:03:26,521 --> 00:03:28,356
- (SHEEP BLEATING)
- (BELLS TOLLING)

19
00:03:29,725 --> 00:03:31,560
(CHICKENS CLUCKING)

20
00:03:36,031 --> 00:03:38,300
MARY (VO): <i>The second eldest
of eight children,</i>

21
00:03:39,234 --> 00:03:41,804
<i>she was the daughter
of a blacksmith and his wife,</i>

22
00:03:41,904 --> 00:03:43,639
<i>residing upon Toad Lane.</i>

23
00:03:45,741 --> 00:03:48,944
<i>Situated beneath the looming
shadow of Christ Church,</i>

24
00:03:49,278 --> 00:03:51,214
<i>Manchester's utmost feared</i>

25
00:03:51,314 --> 00:03:53,582
<i>and favored place
of Christian worship.</i>

26
00:03:56,985 --> 00:03:59,555
Hurry now, William, or they
mightn't find a space for us.

27
00:03:59,655 --> 00:04:01,557
MARY (VO): <i>Wherever she went,</i>

28
00:04:01,657 --> 00:04:04,760
<i>William followed his sister,
adoringly.</i>

29
00:04:05,461 --> 00:04:07,931
<i>As William learned
to keep pace,</i>

30
00:04:08,564 --> 00:04:11,634
<i>Ann and the boy's march
were to be in lockstep.</i>

31
00:04:11,734 --> 00:04:13,502
Again, like this, brother.

32
00:04:18,441 --> 00:04:20,309
(BABY COOING)

33
00:04:23,179 --> 00:04:25,048
(BABY BABBLING)

34
00:04:31,020 --> 00:04:33,389
Bless this food, dear Lord.
We thank you.

35
00:04:33,490 --> 00:04:34,724
- Amen.
- Amen.

36
00:04:34,824 --> 00:04:38,428
(MOTHER HUMMING MELODY)

37
00:04:46,236 --> 00:04:47,971
MARY (VO):
<i>When Ann was a child,</i>

38
00:04:48,071 --> 00:04:51,575
<i>her mind was taken up
with the things of God,</i>

39
00:04:51,675 --> 00:04:54,344
<i>so that she saw
heavenly visions</i>

40
00:04:54,444 --> 00:04:56,046
<i>instead of trifling toys.</i>

41
00:04:57,013 --> 00:04:59,116
(BELL TOLLING)

42
00:04:59,216 --> 00:05:01,818
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

43
00:05:03,553 --> 00:05:05,022
Hurry, William.

44
00:05:05,822 --> 00:05:09,927
The coldly intellectual
Church of England

45
00:05:10,027 --> 00:05:14,131
is more concerned
with ritual and power

46
00:05:14,231 --> 00:05:17,001
than the plight
of the common people

47
00:05:17,101 --> 00:05:20,004
who are at mercy of brutal laws.

48
00:05:20,104 --> 00:05:25,309
A ten-year-old child
can be sentenced to death!

49
00:05:26,210 --> 00:05:28,012
To death!

50
00:05:28,713 --> 00:05:31,549
MARY (VO): <i>Ann had great light
and conviction</i>

51
00:05:31,649 --> 00:05:35,019
<i>concerning the sinfulness
and depravity of human nature.</i>

52
00:05:37,054 --> 00:05:40,825
<i>She put her hands to work
and her heart to God,</i>

53
00:05:41,559 --> 00:05:44,028
<i>laboring tirelessly
without complaint.</i>

54
00:05:45,196 --> 00:05:47,165
- Ann?
- A place for everything,

55
00:05:47,265 --> 00:05:49,033
and everything in its place,
William.

56
00:05:52,070 --> 00:05:53,771
(CHILDREN COUGHING)

57
00:05:59,610 --> 00:06:00,912
WOMAN (VO) <i>: George Whitefield</i>

58
00:06:01,012 --> 00:06:03,248
<i>persistently preached
his sermons</i>

59
00:06:03,348 --> 00:06:05,683
<i>from the steps
of Christ Church.</i>

60
00:06:06,284 --> 00:06:08,719
<i>Ann yearned to dedicate herself</i>

61
00:06:08,820 --> 00:06:11,990
<i>to serving God
with equal fervor.</i>

62
00:06:12,090 --> 00:06:15,393
GEORGE: ...preach the Gospel
to arouse the workers

63
00:06:15,493 --> 00:06:18,163
to awareness of their rights!

64
00:06:18,263 --> 00:06:19,798
WOMAN: What do you
call yourselves?

65
00:06:19,898 --> 00:06:23,802
Because we conduct our worship
by "rule and method,"

66
00:06:23,902 --> 00:06:26,872
some do refer to us
as Methodist.

67
00:06:27,473 --> 00:06:30,275
- (FATHER GRUNTING)
- (BED CREAKING)

68
00:06:32,444 --> 00:06:33,545
MOTHER: Shh!

69
00:06:33,645 --> 00:06:35,180
The children can hear you.

70
00:06:36,948 --> 00:06:39,885
MARY (VO): <i>Ann's hatred
of "fleshly cohabitation"</i>

71
00:06:39,985 --> 00:06:42,454
<i>dated from her earliest youth.</i>

72
00:06:42,554 --> 00:06:44,390
(GRUNTING CONTINUES)

73
00:06:53,865 --> 00:06:56,035
MOTHER: Ann, what has
possessed you this morning?

74
00:06:56,868 --> 00:06:57,970
You--

75
00:06:58,070 --> 00:06:59,805
Speak intelligibly, Ann Lee.

76
00:07:00,973 --> 00:07:02,341
I know what you do to her.

77
00:07:06,713 --> 00:07:08,614
She doesn't mean anything
by it, sweetheart.

78
00:07:12,785 --> 00:07:14,053
Hands on the table.

79
00:07:17,389 --> 00:07:18,424
Flat on the table.

80
00:07:21,494 --> 00:07:22,662
- (SWITCH STRIKING)
- (DOG BARKING)

81
00:07:22,762 --> 00:07:25,765
(BABY CRYING)

82
00:07:27,266 --> 00:07:28,368
MOTHER: Enough.

83
00:07:28,468 --> 00:07:30,236
- (STRIKING CONTINUES)
- (GASPS IN PAIN)

84
00:07:31,938 --> 00:07:33,005
That's enough now.

85
00:07:33,105 --> 00:07:35,074
(STRIKING CONTINUES)

86
00:07:35,174 --> 00:07:37,544
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

87
00:07:37,644 --> 00:07:40,313
(RHYTHMIC CHANTING)

88
00:07:45,818 --> 00:07:48,321
(OVERLAPPING WAILING)

89
00:08:06,606 --> 00:08:09,176
(ROOSTER CROWING)

90
00:08:27,761 --> 00:08:30,298
(SNORING)

91
00:08:35,803 --> 00:08:37,838
I don't have to be
down the mills yet, do I?

92
00:08:37,938 --> 00:08:38,972
(ANN SHUSHING)

93
00:08:39,073 --> 00:08:40,841
It's not light yet.

94
00:08:41,242 --> 00:08:43,177
I want to visit
my mother's resting place

95
00:08:43,277 --> 00:08:45,179
on the way to the infirmary.

96
00:08:45,279 --> 00:08:48,049
Uncle William will walk with you
to the mill this morning.

97
00:08:49,383 --> 00:08:53,521
And Nancy,
if Uncle William's slow to rise,

98
00:08:53,621 --> 00:08:55,189
clutch him by the nose.

99
00:08:56,057 --> 00:08:57,658
Blame it on Auntie Ann.

100
00:08:57,759 --> 00:08:59,928
(ROOSTER CROWING)

101
00:09:05,266 --> 00:09:07,468
(GOATS BLEATING)

102
00:09:07,569 --> 00:09:08,803
(BELL TOLLING)

103
00:09:13,274 --> 00:09:15,977
(VILLAGERS CHATTERING)

104
00:09:42,871 --> 00:09:46,141
MARY (VO): <i>To be free
of the mill's wearying labor,</i>

105
00:09:46,241 --> 00:09:50,312
<i>Ann found herself in service as
a cook at the local infirmary.</i>

106
00:09:53,883 --> 00:09:56,551
<i>In the scant leisure
she possessed,</i>

107
00:09:57,152 --> 00:10:01,356
<i>she yearned to find purpose
amidst the dullness of her lot.</i>

108
00:10:06,195 --> 00:10:08,063
(MAN COUGHING)

109
00:10:09,732 --> 00:10:12,435
WOMAN: No! No!

110
00:10:12,535 --> 00:10:14,404
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

111
00:10:16,772 --> 00:10:18,974
(OVERLAPPING SHOUTING)

112
00:10:21,277 --> 00:10:22,678
Pardon me.

113
00:10:22,778 --> 00:10:24,247
The invalids
are having something

114
00:10:24,347 --> 00:10:26,316
of a collective episode,
Miss Ann.

115
00:10:26,416 --> 00:10:28,184
My companions
are waiting for me.

116
00:10:28,284 --> 00:10:29,285
WILLIAM: <i>Make haste, sister.</i>

117
00:10:29,485 --> 00:10:30,920
The assembly mightn't
welcome dalliers.

118
00:10:31,020 --> 00:10:33,123
When have you known me
to dally, William?

119
00:10:33,223 --> 00:10:35,758
There was some gruesome
commotion at hospital.

120
00:10:35,858 --> 00:10:36,959
Gruesome?
Was someone injured?

121
00:10:37,060 --> 00:10:38,628
A patient, self-harmed.

122
00:10:38,728 --> 00:10:40,997
They barred the exits
of all faculty

123
00:10:41,097 --> 00:10:42,432
until the coroner arrived.

124
00:10:44,034 --> 00:10:47,938
Here, quickly.
Provisions from the kitchen.

125
00:10:48,038 --> 00:10:50,140
Nicked an egg for each of you,
and some bread.

126
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:52,208
- Nicked?
- No, dear.

127
00:10:52,308 --> 00:10:54,711
- I just saved it from waste.
- WILLIAM: Let's take our supper

128
00:10:54,811 --> 00:10:56,546
as we tram over mountain
and moorland.

129
00:10:56,647 --> 00:10:59,215
- (COWS LOWING)
- (SHEEP BLEATING)

130
00:10:59,315 --> 00:11:00,784
No time to wash up, Nancy?

131
00:11:00,884 --> 00:11:02,385
No, Auntie.

132
00:11:02,786 --> 00:11:05,889
MARY (VO): <i>Always seeking
a more harmonious consonance</i>

133
00:11:05,989 --> 00:11:07,791
<i>between her faith in God</i>

134
00:11:07,891 --> 00:11:10,093
<i>and the religious
establishment,</i>

135
00:11:10,193 --> 00:11:13,764
<i>she attended a series
of local revival meetings</i>

136
00:11:13,864 --> 00:11:15,999
<i>hosted by Jane
and James Wardley.</i>

137
00:11:16,099 --> 00:11:17,268
Good evening.

138
00:11:18,602 --> 00:11:20,036
I would be remiss
if I were first

139
00:11:20,136 --> 00:11:21,872
not to thank Mr. John Townley

140
00:11:21,972 --> 00:11:23,774
for hosting us
in his beautiful home.

141
00:11:26,277 --> 00:11:28,412
For those new here tonight,

142
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:32,416
perhaps you're unaccustomed
to hearing the voice

143
00:11:32,516 --> 00:11:35,186
and seeing the demeanor
of a woman preacher.

144
00:11:35,286 --> 00:11:37,922
So James and I thought
you might find this passage

145
00:11:38,022 --> 00:11:39,857
particularly illuminating.

146
00:11:41,225 --> 00:11:42,593
From Jeremiah...

147
00:11:47,098 --> 00:11:52,303
"How long wilt thou go about,
O you backsliding daughter?

148
00:11:52,403 --> 00:11:55,640
For the Lord hath created
a new thing on earth,

149
00:11:56,708 --> 00:12:01,345
a woman shall compass a man..."

150
00:12:01,445 --> 00:12:06,050
Christ's spirit first appeared
in the form of a man, Jesus,

151
00:12:06,150 --> 00:12:08,252
but will eventually reappear,

152
00:12:08,353 --> 00:12:11,055
to fulfill the promise
of the second coming,

153
00:12:11,155 --> 00:12:13,090
in the form of a woman.

154
00:12:13,190 --> 00:12:16,594
As we were all created
in his likeness,

155
00:12:16,694 --> 00:12:20,965
God must be both
male and female.

156
00:12:21,065 --> 00:12:22,400
WOMAN: Yes!

157
00:12:23,201 --> 00:12:25,937
You there,
we have not seen you before.

158
00:12:27,105 --> 00:12:29,507
May I ask,
what's drawn you to us?

159
00:12:29,607 --> 00:12:32,577
I am Ann Lee.
This is my brother, William Lee,

160
00:12:32,677 --> 00:12:35,313
and my late sister's daughter,
Nancy Lee.

161
00:12:35,413 --> 00:12:36,414
Yes?

162
00:12:37,649 --> 00:12:38,683
We've come because--

163
00:12:38,783 --> 00:12:40,118
"For he who confesses,

164
00:12:40,218 --> 00:12:43,055
shams are over
and realities have begun;

165
00:12:44,289 --> 00:12:47,025
he has exteriorized
his rottenness."

166
00:12:47,125 --> 00:12:48,526
Tell us why you've come.

167
00:12:49,394 --> 00:12:50,696
Bare yourself to us.

168
00:12:51,730 --> 00:12:52,598
Well...

169
00:12:55,033 --> 00:12:57,703
many times
when I'm about my work,

170
00:12:59,472 --> 00:13:02,641
I feel my soul overwhelmed
with sorrow.

171
00:13:02,741 --> 00:13:05,644
I will work as long as I can
to keep it concealed

172
00:13:05,744 --> 00:13:08,013
and then I will run
to get out of sight,

173
00:13:08,113 --> 00:13:09,081
lest someone should pity me

174
00:13:09,181 --> 00:13:11,016
with that pity
that God does not.

175
00:13:12,785 --> 00:13:18,424
Welcome to the Wardley Society,
Ann, William, and Nancy.

176
00:13:18,524 --> 00:13:20,526
Yes, welcome.

177
00:13:20,626 --> 00:13:21,827
I'm Father James Wardley

178
00:13:21,927 --> 00:13:24,030
and this is my wife,
Mother Jane.

179
00:13:26,932 --> 00:13:31,704
When you confess your sins,
you must labor to remember

180
00:13:31,804 --> 00:13:35,274
the time when and the place
where you committed them.

181
00:13:35,374 --> 00:13:36,843
And when you have
confessed them,

182
00:13:36,943 --> 00:13:38,711
you will cry to God

183
00:13:38,812 --> 00:13:41,480
to know if your confession
is accepted.

184
00:13:41,580 --> 00:13:43,683
And by crying to God,

185
00:13:43,783 --> 00:13:46,552
you will eventually travel
out of your loss.

186
00:13:48,655 --> 00:13:50,356
James Whittaker, please rise...

187
00:13:51,991 --> 00:13:54,393
and share with us
your unflinching testimony.

188
00:13:59,198 --> 00:14:02,569
Go on, James.
Give your grief to God.

189
00:14:08,708 --> 00:14:11,110
Some years ago, I have by chance

190
00:14:11,211 --> 00:14:13,213
seen my sister bathing and,
at once,

191
00:14:13,313 --> 00:14:20,087
I was filled with a tremor
throughout my whole being.

192
00:14:20,187 --> 00:14:25,059
My body quaked
at the sight of her

193
00:14:25,159 --> 00:14:26,560
like a split peach.

194
00:14:28,728 --> 00:14:32,499
It is improper
because she is a child.

195
00:14:32,599 --> 00:14:36,804
It is wrong because she is
my own flesh and blood.

196
00:14:39,273 --> 00:14:43,811
(REPEATEDLY EXHALING SHARPLY)

197
00:14:43,911 --> 00:14:45,846
(WHITTAKER WAILING)

198
00:14:45,946 --> 00:14:47,815
(WOMAN WAILING LOUDLY)

199
00:14:49,349 --> 00:14:51,986
(WHITAKER GRUNTING RHYTHMICALLY)

200
00:14:54,221 --> 00:14:56,691
(WOMAN CONTINUES WAILING)

201
00:15:07,702 --> 00:15:10,471
MARY (VO): <i>The Wardleys
had been devout Quakers,</i>

202
00:15:10,571 --> 00:15:13,108
<i>dedicated to the belief
that true religion</i>

203
00:15:13,208 --> 00:15:15,510
<i>comes from inward experience.</i>

204
00:15:15,610 --> 00:15:18,179
(WOMAN WAILING WILDLY)

205
00:15:18,279 --> 00:15:20,481
(WHITTAKER SHOUTING)

206
00:15:27,889 --> 00:15:29,557
MARY (VO): <i>But had left
to form their own,</i>

207
00:15:29,657 --> 00:15:33,061
<i>more dynamic,
religious community.</i>

208
00:15:33,161 --> 00:15:36,464
(WOMAN SHRIEKING)

209
00:15:36,564 --> 00:15:38,967
<i>They were known
as the Shaking Quakers,</i>

210
00:15:39,067 --> 00:15:41,937
<i>or Shakers,
as the locals referred to them,</i>

211
00:15:42,037 --> 00:15:43,805
<i>because of the shaking
and dancing</i>

212
00:15:43,905 --> 00:15:45,841
<i>that characterized
their worship.</i>

213
00:15:45,941 --> 00:15:47,776
(BOTH CONTINUE WAILING)

214
00:15:49,811 --> 00:15:51,647
(ALL GASPING IN RHYTHM)

215
00:15:53,349 --> 00:15:57,586
(WOMAN SPEAKING IN TONGUES)

216
00:16:07,729 --> 00:16:10,866
(WOMAN SHRIEKS AND LAUGHS)

217
00:16:11,600 --> 00:16:14,636
(RHYTHMIC CHANTING
BREATHS CONTINUE AND FADE)

218
00:16:14,736 --> 00:16:17,773
MARY (VO): <i>Ann Lee had at last
discovered a community</i>

219
00:16:17,873 --> 00:16:19,808
<i>that espoused her beliefs,</i>

220
00:16:19,909 --> 00:16:21,844
<i>and she, in turn,</i>

221
00:16:21,944 --> 00:16:25,314
<i>embraced their principles
wholeheartedly.</i>

222
00:16:25,414 --> 00:16:27,249
<i>♪ La-la-la-la-la-la
La, la-la-la ♪</i>

223
00:16:27,349 --> 00:16:29,085
<i>♪ La, la-la-la-la-la, la-la ♪</i>

224
00:16:29,185 --> 00:16:30,987
<i>♪ La-la-la-la-la-la
La, la-la ♪</i>

225
00:16:31,087 --> 00:16:32,722
<i>♪ La-la-la-la-la-la ♪</i>

226
00:16:32,822 --> 00:16:37,594
(VOCALIZING CONTINUES)

227
00:16:37,694 --> 00:16:40,062
MARY (VO): <i>There, she caught
the eye of a man</i>

228
00:16:40,162 --> 00:16:42,999
<i>of the same faith,
Abraham,</i>

229
00:16:43,099 --> 00:16:45,167
<i>a blacksmith like her father.</i>

230
00:16:45,267 --> 00:16:47,003
(VOCALIZING CONTINUES)

231
00:16:50,540 --> 00:16:53,109
(HAMMERS CLANGING)

232
00:17:01,284 --> 00:17:03,253
(VOCALIZING CONTINUES)

233
00:17:05,955 --> 00:17:07,824
(WOMEN SHRIEKING)

234
00:17:25,442 --> 00:17:27,377
(WOMAN GRUNTING)

235
00:17:28,378 --> 00:17:34,184
(WOMAN SHRIEKING)

236
00:17:37,420 --> 00:17:40,057
(VOCALIZING CONTINUES)

237
00:17:56,507 --> 00:17:58,376
(WOMAN WAILING)

238
00:18:14,859 --> 00:18:16,727
(MAN WAILING)

239
00:18:32,310 --> 00:18:34,112
MARY (VO): <i>She later
married Abraham.</i>

240
00:18:36,147 --> 00:18:40,018
<i>Mary Partington bore witness
to the marriage ceremony,</i>

241
