<i>♪ Till my soul's filled
with love ♪</i>

487
00:39:44,471 --> 00:39:51,312
<i>♪ Love and sweet peace ♪</i>

488
00:39:52,847 --> 00:39:55,416
<i>♪ I hunger and thirst ♪</i>

489
00:39:55,516 --> 00:39:57,719
<i>♪ I hunger and thirst ♪</i>

490
00:39:57,819 --> 00:40:00,588
<i>♪ After true righteousness ♪</i>

491
00:40:00,688 --> 00:40:03,090
<i>♪ I hunger and thirst ♪</i>

492
00:40:03,190 --> 00:40:06,427
<i>♪ I hunger and thirst ♪</i>

493
00:40:06,528 --> 00:40:08,362
WOMAN: <i>* And thirst ♪</i>

494
00:40:08,463 --> 00:40:10,832
ANN AND CHORUS:
<i>♪ I hunger and thirst ♪</i>

495
00:40:10,932 --> 00:40:13,134
<i>♪ I hunger and thirst ♪</i>

496
00:40:13,234 --> 00:40:16,037
<i>♪ After true righteousness ♪</i>

497
00:40:16,137 --> 00:40:18,706
<i>♪ I hunger and thirst ♪</i>

498
00:40:18,806 --> 00:40:23,010
<i>♪ I hunger and thirst ♪</i>

499
00:40:26,548 --> 00:40:33,055
<i>♪ I hunger and thirst ♪</i>

500
00:40:33,155 --> 00:40:36,058
MARY (VO): <i>And there appeared
a great wonder in Heaven,</i>

501
00:40:36,158 --> 00:40:40,528
<i>a woman clothed with the sun
and the moon under her feet.</i>

502
00:40:40,628 --> 00:40:45,067
<i>And upon her head,
a crown of twelve stars.</i>

503
00:40:45,167 --> 00:40:47,502
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

504
00:40:51,173 --> 00:40:55,578
MAN: Please, sir,
I am aching with hungriness.

505
00:40:55,678 --> 00:40:56,812
What have you done to her?

506
00:41:01,316 --> 00:41:03,218
Oh, you're warm.
You're breathing.

507
00:41:03,318 --> 00:41:05,253
Wake up, Sister. Hear my voice.

508
00:41:05,353 --> 00:41:06,321
It's me, William.

509
00:41:07,355 --> 00:41:08,323
Here, drink this.

510
00:41:10,225 --> 00:41:12,027
You must cut your locks,
Brother.

511
00:41:13,195 --> 00:41:15,564
I need to see the Wardleys
forthwith.

512
00:41:24,307 --> 00:41:26,309
MAN: Get ready to forgive
your sisters and brothers

513
00:41:26,409 --> 00:41:28,844
on the first intonations
of repentance.

514
00:41:30,980 --> 00:41:33,349
I was covered in a downy hair,

515
00:41:33,449 --> 00:41:36,419
which I shed as I was reborn

516
00:41:36,519 --> 00:41:40,423
into the most
astonishing visions,

517
00:41:41,490 --> 00:41:45,862
and divine manifestations
that were presented to me

518
00:41:45,962 --> 00:41:49,298
in so clear and striking
a manner,

519
00:41:49,398 --> 00:41:53,570
that the whole spiritual world
was displayed before me.

520
00:41:55,004 --> 00:41:57,173
And in
that soul-splitting moment,

521
00:41:58,575 --> 00:42:01,945
I felt the cause
of all suffering and...

522
00:42:02,045 --> 00:42:04,481
and the mystery of all evil, revealed.

523
00:42:05,549 --> 00:42:06,850
What did you see?

524
00:42:07,016 --> 00:42:10,186
I... First I saw Adam and Eve
in the Garden of Eden.

525
00:42:11,521 --> 00:42:14,090
I watched them defy God

526
00:42:14,191 --> 00:42:17,093
and commit the forbidden
carnal act.

527
00:42:17,194 --> 00:42:19,929
And then I witnessed
their expulsion from the garden

528
00:42:20,029 --> 00:42:22,266
by an enraged deity.

529
00:42:22,699 --> 00:42:25,402
And all at once, I understood

530
00:42:25,502 --> 00:42:28,405
that there is one single cause

531
00:42:28,505 --> 00:42:31,141
for humanity's separation
from God:

532
00:42:32,409 --> 00:42:34,044
fornication.

533
00:42:38,816 --> 00:42:39,784
ABRAHAM: Ann.

534
00:42:41,351 --> 00:42:44,989
I, uh... I'm contrite
for coming only now.

535
00:42:46,356 --> 00:42:47,792
The mill received
a hefty contract

536
00:42:47,892 --> 00:42:50,194
for lattice fences, you see.

537
00:42:50,294 --> 00:42:51,762
We've been inundated

538
00:42:51,862 --> 00:42:53,297
with iron and steel
from the forge.

539
00:42:54,398 --> 00:42:55,866
JANE: Ann Lee was relaying to us

540
00:42:55,966 --> 00:42:58,703
that her earlier suspicions
have been confirmed.

541
00:42:59,470 --> 00:43:02,039
She's discovered there is
only one way for humanity

542
00:43:02,139 --> 00:43:03,841
to recover its lost state.

543
00:43:03,941 --> 00:43:05,576
(RASPING COUGH)

544
00:43:05,676 --> 00:43:06,977
JAMES: My understanding...

545
00:43:08,879 --> 00:43:10,748
is to enter
a new age of spirituality,

546
00:43:10,848 --> 00:43:12,417
men and women must abstain

547
00:43:12,517 --> 00:43:14,652
from all lustful gratification
of the flesh.

548
00:43:15,853 --> 00:43:19,557
Self-denial by celibacy

549
00:43:20,158 --> 00:43:22,827
would be the first essential
for all men and women

550
00:43:22,927 --> 00:43:26,031
who want to gain
the spiritual strength

551
00:43:26,131 --> 00:43:27,765
to reach God.

552
00:43:29,935 --> 00:43:31,469
Jane and I
are in agreement with you,

553
00:43:33,071 --> 00:43:34,172
Mother Ann.

554
00:43:34,272 --> 00:43:35,640
(SIGHS SOFTLY)

555
00:43:35,741 --> 00:43:36,574
"Mother"?

556
00:43:37,508 --> 00:43:38,910
WILLIAM: I love my Mother.

557
00:43:39,577 --> 00:43:42,413
She is my sister,
but she has become my Mother.

558
00:43:43,114 --> 00:43:45,216
And the Lord God made me
to love her.

559
00:43:47,986 --> 00:43:49,387
(ANN PANTING)

560
00:43:49,488 --> 00:43:51,890
During my period
of incarceration,

561
00:43:53,925 --> 00:43:57,228
a sense of release
swept over me,

562
00:43:58,229 --> 00:44:01,633
and my whole being

563
00:44:02,934 --> 00:44:06,938
was suffused
with inner harmony and peace.

564
00:44:08,474 --> 00:44:12,578
And I feel that all my sins
are now forgiven.

565
00:44:13,979 --> 00:44:14,846
And that...

566
00:44:16,348 --> 00:44:20,352
this is the vision
I shall carry in my heart

567
00:44:20,452 --> 00:44:22,088
for the rest of my days.

568
00:44:25,157 --> 00:44:26,492
Brother Abraham,

569
00:44:27,259 --> 00:44:29,261
come and kneel
before our Mother Ann.

570
00:45:27,955 --> 00:45:30,057
We'll have to say
our farewells tonight.

571
00:45:34,928 --> 00:45:36,897
Been a great friend to me,
Jacob.

572
00:45:51,312 --> 00:45:54,548
<i>♪ So I freely give the whole ♪</i>

573
00:45:57,518 --> 00:45:59,187
<i>♪ Of my body and... ♪</i>

574
00:46:01,355 --> 00:46:03,357
<i>♪ And my soul ♪</i>

575
00:46:06,527 --> 00:46:10,531
<i>♪ To the Lord, God ♪</i>

576
00:46:12,233 --> 00:46:13,601
<i>♪ Amen ♪</i>

577
00:46:13,767 --> 00:46:16,637
MAN: <i>God is faithful and just
to forgive us our sins</i>

578
00:46:16,737 --> 00:46:19,307
and to cleanse us
from all unrighteousness...

579
00:46:19,407 --> 00:46:21,475
MARY (VO): <i>And so,
they set forth with vigor</i>

580
00:46:21,575 --> 00:46:23,311
<i>to enlighten all of Manchester</i>

581
00:46:23,411 --> 00:46:25,246
<i>- that she, Ann...</i>
- MAN: What is this?

582
00:46:25,346 --> 00:46:27,048
MARY (VO):
<i>Christ's Second Coming...</i>

583
00:46:27,148 --> 00:46:28,182
<i>- was among them...</i>
- What brings you to our doors?

584
00:46:28,282 --> 00:46:30,218
<i>and here
to liberate the community</i>

585
00:46:30,318 --> 00:46:31,853
<i>from the moral failings</i>

586
00:46:31,953 --> 00:46:34,255
<i>and oppressive doctrines
of the Church of England.</i>

587
00:46:34,355 --> 00:46:37,091
It is not I that speak.

588
00:46:37,191 --> 00:46:39,160
- It is Christ who dwells in me.
- Blasphemy!

589
00:46:39,260 --> 00:46:40,294
Get down from there
this very instant!

590
00:46:40,394 --> 00:46:42,163
I have been in fine valleys

591
00:46:42,263 --> 00:46:44,098
- with Christ as a lover.
- Blasphemy!

592
00:46:44,198 --> 00:46:46,368
I am married
to the Lord Jesus Christ!

593
00:46:46,468 --> 00:46:50,505
He is my head and my husband,
and I have no other!

594
00:46:50,605 --> 00:46:52,841
- Get down from there!
- I have walked, hand in hand,

595
00:46:52,941 --> 00:46:55,310
with God in Heaven.

596
00:46:55,410 --> 00:46:57,412
Get down from there
this very instant!

597
00:46:57,512 --> 00:46:59,514
You will hang for this,
young lady!

598
00:46:59,614 --> 00:47:01,350
- It's blasphemy!
- WOMAN: Blasphemy!

599
00:47:04,119 --> 00:47:05,454
(YELLS IN PAIN)

600
00:47:05,554 --> 00:47:07,722
TIDESWELL: What is the woman
charged with?

601
00:47:07,822 --> 00:47:09,291
- MAN: The charge is assault.
- WILLIAM: 'Tis a lie!

602
00:47:09,391 --> 00:47:10,592
- My sister is a pacifist!
- MAN: And willfully

603
00:47:10,692 --> 00:47:12,962
and contemptuously
disturbing divine service

604
00:47:13,062 --> 00:47:14,363
- at Christ Church.
- JAMES: 'Tis a lie!

605
00:47:14,596 --> 00:47:16,331
WOMAN: She claims herself wed
to the Lord Jesus Christ!

606
00:47:16,431 --> 00:47:17,599
Quiet, now.

607
00:47:17,699 --> 00:47:19,634
ANN: May I speak for myself,
Your Worship?

608
00:47:19,735 --> 00:47:20,936
You may.

609
00:47:21,636 --> 00:47:24,807
I live in celibacy,
and am wed to the Lord,

610
00:47:24,907 --> 00:47:27,076
much like a nun
of your own church.

611
00:47:28,410 --> 00:47:31,246
We have rejected
sinful pleasures of the flesh

612
00:47:31,346 --> 00:47:33,649
and only share our love
with Jesus.

613
00:47:34,484 --> 00:47:36,385
And Jesus spoke to me.

614
00:47:37,720 --> 00:47:44,059
(SPEAKING LATIN)

615
00:47:44,159 --> 00:47:45,995
MARY (VO):
<i>According to one legend,</i>

616
00:47:46,095 --> 00:47:49,732
<i>she spoke to them that night
in 12 languages,</i>

617
00:47:49,832 --> 00:47:53,436
<i>including Greek, Latin,
Hebrew, and French.</i>

618
00:47:53,536 --> 00:47:57,640
<i>By another account, she spoke
in 72 different tongues.</i>

619
00:47:57,740 --> 00:48:00,743
<i>History states as a fact,
however,</i>

620
00:48:00,843 --> 00:48:03,213
<i>that Mother Ann spoke</i>

621
00:48:03,313 --> 00:48:06,582
<i>and manifested
such evident power of God</i>

622
00:48:06,682 --> 00:48:08,751
<i>that the four ministers
of Christ Church</i>

623
00:48:08,851 --> 00:48:11,187
<i>thought it only proper
to dismiss her.</i>

624
00:48:11,287 --> 00:48:12,889
Mother Ann,
I've posted your penalties.

625
00:48:12,989 --> 00:48:13,957
You're free to go.

626
00:48:14,057 --> 00:48:16,092
They are our penalties,
Mr. Townley.

627
00:48:16,192 --> 00:48:17,393
It is our mission.

628
00:48:17,493 --> 00:48:19,963
(OVERLAPPING SHOUTING)

629
00:48:20,063 --> 00:48:21,431
This is beneath you!
Shame on you!

630
00:48:21,531 --> 00:48:23,066
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

631
00:48:23,166 --> 00:48:25,569
Inventive in their reproach,
dear Brother.

632
00:48:26,603 --> 00:48:29,005
MARY (VO): <i>While some welcomed
the verdict with joy,</i>

633
00:48:29,105 --> 00:48:31,842
<i>the thought of a woman preacher
infuriated others.</i>

634
00:48:31,942 --> 00:48:33,677
Do not run!

635
00:48:33,777 --> 00:48:34,811
MAN: Shame on you!

636
00:48:35,612 --> 00:48:36,613
WOMAN: You're a witch!

637
00:48:38,148 --> 00:48:40,283
(WATER DRIPPING)

638
00:48:48,024 --> 00:48:49,025
Thank you, Brother.

639
00:48:51,328 --> 00:48:52,463
Where is your husband?

640
00:48:53,063 --> 00:48:56,500
At the smithy,
morning and night.

641
00:48:56,600 --> 00:48:58,935
Ah, yes.
Whenever my sister is imperiled,

642
00:48:59,036 --> 00:49:02,806
Abraham finds himself
predisposed.

643
00:49:02,907 --> 00:49:05,309
You must try and be
more understanding of him.

644
00:49:06,277 --> 00:49:07,678
He's been through so much.

645
00:49:08,813 --> 00:49:09,947
As have you.

646
00:49:13,818 --> 00:49:15,519
Read me the morning paper,
will you?

647
00:49:24,596 --> 00:49:26,163
There's something
on George Whitefield,

648
00:49:26,263 --> 00:49:27,965
the man that used to preach
outside of Christ Church.

649
00:49:28,065 --> 00:49:29,033
What's it say?

650
00:49:29,834 --> 00:49:31,368
Read it aloud to me.

651
00:49:32,303 --> 00:49:34,071
Courtesy of a raven messenger.

652
00:49:34,472 --> 00:49:35,773
What am I looking at?

653
00:49:36,374 --> 00:49:38,643
The piece
on Reverend George Whitefield.

654
00:49:38,743 --> 00:49:39,911
The Methodist?

655
00:49:40,011 --> 00:49:42,347
He has returned
from his fifth trip to America.

656
00:49:45,950 --> 00:49:47,852
"With blazing eloquence,

657
00:49:47,952 --> 00:49:50,588
Whitefield describes
opportunities for rebirth

658
00:49:50,688 --> 00:49:52,057
of the spirit in America.

659
00:49:53,025 --> 00:49:54,092
'The colonies,' he says,

660
00:49:54,192 --> 00:49:56,894
'will one day
gain their independence,

661
00:49:56,995 --> 00:50:00,065
and then freedom of conscience
will be secured

662
00:50:00,165 --> 00:50:03,368
for all people to worship God
without hindrance or--'"

663
00:50:03,468 --> 00:50:05,270
Am I to continue?

664
00:50:05,703 --> 00:50:07,439
You don't grasp
its significance?

665
00:50:08,540 --> 00:50:11,009
I have seen a chosen people
waiting for us in New England,

666
00:50:11,109 --> 00:50:12,978
and I know that God wants us

667
00:50:13,078 --> 00:50:15,681
to take the Millennial Church
to America.

668
00:50:15,781 --> 00:50:18,817
And that he will aid us
in this enormous undertaking.

669
00:50:18,917 --> 00:50:20,218
Are you mad?

670
00:50:20,318 --> 00:50:21,720
Mr. Townley!

671
00:50:22,488 --> 00:50:23,889
Father James,

672
00:50:23,989 --> 00:50:27,292
you cannot possibly
expect me to foot this bill.

673
00:50:27,993 --> 00:50:30,529
Nor to undertake such a journey
at my age.

674
00:50:31,063 --> 00:50:33,832
My entire life,
not to mention my trade,

675
00:50:33,932 --> 00:50:35,634
is here in Manchester.

676
00:50:35,734 --> 00:50:38,671
I am unable to do our good work
amongst the Mancunian denizens

677
00:50:38,771 --> 00:50:42,275
because their hearts and minds
are spoilt.

678
00:50:42,875 --> 00:50:46,679
I cannot preach without
being harassed and assaulted.

679
00:50:46,779 --> 00:50:48,281
Violated.

680
00:50:49,482 --> 00:50:51,817
They will kill me, eventually.

681
00:50:51,917 --> 00:50:55,188
Mother Ann, you have my utmost
respect and admiration--

682
00:50:55,288 --> 00:50:58,024
Mr. Townley, it's not
the dying part which minds me.

683
00:50:59,225 --> 00:51:01,094
I have lost
four beautiful children

684
00:51:01,194 --> 00:51:04,063
with whom I anxiously wait
to be reunited.

685
00:51:04,163 --> 00:51:05,598
It's the lost time.

686
00:51:06,499 --> 00:51:08,334
Time to spread the word.

687
00:51:08,935 --> 00:51:11,304
It is the lost voice
which minds me.

688
00:51:13,940 --> 00:51:16,976
Thank you for your time

689
00:51:17,076 --> 00:51:19,646
and generous access
to your home, Mr. Townley.

690
00:51:21,147 --> 00:51:22,381
James--

691
00:51:22,482 --> 00:51:24,551
Father James.

692
00:51:25,351 --> 00:51:28,555
Look, my brother-in-law,
he's a farmer.

693
00:51:28,655 --> 00:51:31,391
He's attended several
of our more sizable meetings

694
00:51:31,491 --> 00:51:32,726
here at the house.

695
00:51:34,328 --> 00:51:35,762
He's a shy man

696
00:51:35,862 --> 00:51:37,997
and not a very polished
gentleman, perhaps,

697
00:51:38,097 --> 00:51:41,301
but where there's muck,
there's brass, you see.

698
00:51:41,401 --> 00:51:42,502
Yes?

699
00:51:43,002 --> 00:51:46,840
Well, he has sometimes inquired
to me privately

700
00:51:46,940 --> 00:51:49,209
as to how he might aid us
in our quest here.

701
00:51:50,644 --> 00:51:52,479
Why have you never brought
this prospective sponsor

702
00:51:52,579 --> 00:51:54,081
to our attention?

703
00:51:54,181 --> 00:51:56,851
It seemed, at the time,
we had enough for our need.

704
00:51:57,451 --> 00:51:59,586
Your brother-in-law
is John Hocknell.

705
00:51:59,686 --> 00:52:00,821
JOHN: That's right.

706
00:52:02,522 --> 00:52:04,224
You've spoken with him?

707
00:52:04,324 --> 00:52:06,426
He approached Mother Jane and I
some time ago.

708
00:52:06,526 --> 00:52:09,196
But we boasted then
of our loyalties to you.

709
00:52:15,603 --> 00:52:17,337
Our quest is here no longer.

710
00:52:17,438 --> 00:52:18,405
Mother Ann.

711
00:52:27,615 --> 00:52:30,084
MARY (VO): <i>It was decided
that James and Jane Wardley</i>

712
00:52:30,184 --> 00:52:32,086
<i>should stay the course
in Manchester,</i>

713
00:52:33,854 --> 00:52:35,290
<i>though their hearts ached
on the day</i>

714
00:52:35,390 --> 00:52:37,024
<i>of their Mother Ann's
departure.</i>

715
00:52:58,780 --> 00:53:00,248
MARY (VO): <i>Their berths
aboard the</i> Mariah

716
00:53:00,348 --> 00:53:02,450
<i>were obtained at little cost,</i>

717
00:53:02,851 --> 00:53:04,620
<i>the ship having been condemned.</i>

718
00:53:07,088 --> 00:53:08,957
<i>Unsound in the eyes of men,</i>

719
00:53:10,626 --> 00:53:13,695
<i>yet sufficient for those led
by the Spirit.</i>

720
00:53:13,795 --> 00:53:19,401
<i>It set sail from Liverpool
on May 19th, 1774.</i>

721
00:53:23,171 --> 00:53:25,274
<i>Their newfound patron,</i>

722
00:53:25,374 --> 00:53:27,543
<i>John Hocknell's
means were modest,</i>

723
00:53:27,643 --> 00:53:29,811
<i>but his devotion was boundless.</i>

724
00:53:29,911 --> 00:53:31,847
<i>He'd have moved mountains
for Mother Ann,</i>

725
00:53:31,947 --> 00:53:33,449
<i>let alone, moved house.</i>

726
00:53:40,522 --> 00:53:42,524
<i>Without so much as a nudge,</i>

727
00:53:42,624 --> 00:53:45,527
<i>Hocknell left everyone
and everything behind,</i>

728
00:53:45,627 --> 00:53:48,030
<i>aside from
his know-nothing heir, Richard,</i>

729
00:53:48,130 --> 00:53:49,331
<i>and his billfold.</i>

730
00:53:49,431 --> 00:53:50,766
(GOATS BLEATING)

731
00:53:56,072 --> 00:53:57,707
(MAN COUGHING)

732
00:54:00,242 --> 00:54:02,712
MARY (VO): <i>Abraham never did
seem aught more</i>

733
00:54:02,812 --> 00:54:05,447
<i>than a mere perplexed observer</i>

734
00:54:05,548 --> 00:54:07,950
<i>of his wife's
theological virtues.</i>

735
00:54:09,452 --> 00:54:13,322
(MAN COUGHING)

736
00:54:27,870 --> 00:54:29,672
<i>He had, indeed,</i>

737
00:54:29,772 --> 00:54:33,610
<i>been most uncertain regarding
the voyage to America,</i>

738
00:54:35,078 --> 00:54:39,149
<i>yet was swayed
by the promise of innovation</i>

739
00:54:39,249 --> 00:54:42,552
<i>in the working of metals
upon the shores of New York.</i>

740
00:54:42,652 --> 00:54:44,054
(BOAT HULL CREAKING)

741
00:54:44,154 --> 00:54:45,989
(MAN COUGHING)

742
00:54:47,124 --> 00:54:48,959
- Mother?
- Hmm?

743
00:54:49,059 --> 00:54:51,294
There's something
I have been wanting to tell you.

744
00:54:51,394 --> 00:54:53,063
Go on, Mary.

745
00:54:53,864 --> 00:54:56,266
On our penultimate night
in Manchester,

746
00:54:56,366 --> 00:54:58,335
following a 13-kilometer trek
on foot

747
00:54:58,435 --> 00:54:59,536
from Brother Hocknell's farm

748
00:54:59,703 --> 00:55:02,139
to transport his belongings
to the ports,

749
00:55:02,239 --> 00:55:04,775
James Whittaker and I
were resting by the roadside

750
00:55:04,875 --> 00:55:06,276
when a vision appeared to him.

751
00:55:07,277 --> 00:55:08,679
Is that so?

752
00:55:09,413 --> 00:55:13,050
He saw a large tree
"whose leaves," he said,

753
00:55:13,150 --> 00:55:14,985
"shone with such a brightness

754
00:55:15,085 --> 00:55:18,088
that made it appear
like a burning torch."

755
00:55:19,923 --> 00:55:22,593
He took this to mean that he was
to help plant the tree of faith

756
00:55:22,693 --> 00:55:24,061
in the New World.

757
00:55:26,864 --> 00:55:30,734
We will plant a great big tree,
with deep and solid roots.

758
00:55:30,834 --> 00:55:31,835
MARY: Mm.

759
00:55:31,935 --> 00:55:33,972
Go to sleep now, Mary.

760
00:55:34,072 --> 00:55:35,473
And I'll be sure Mr. Hocknell

761
00:55:35,573 --> 00:55:37,275
never has you
carrying his bags again.

762
00:55:37,375 --> 00:55:38,476
(MARY CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

763
00:55:43,247 --> 00:55:49,788
NANCY: <i>* Today, today
Is my own time ♪</i>

764
00:55:51,823 --> 00:55:58,029
<i>♪ Tomorrow can't be reckoned ♪</i>

765
00:55:59,631 --> 00:56:06,037
<i>♪ And what is past
Cannot return ♪</i>

766
00:56:07,372 --> 00:56:14,212
<i>♪ Though much to be regretted ♪</i>

767
00:56:16,548 --> 00:56:23,322
<i>♪ Today, today is my own time ♪</i>

768
00:56:24,423 --> 00:56:30,329
<i>♪ Tomorrow can't be reckoned ♪</i>

769
00:56:32,231 --> 00:56:39,004
<i>♪ And what is past
Cannot return ♪</i>

770
00:56:40,039 --> 00:56:46,812
<i>♪ Though much to be regretted ♪</i>

771
00:56:48,614 --> 00:56:55,354
BOTH: <i>* Then let me
Well improve each day ♪</i>

772
00:56:56,489 --> 00:57:02,327
<i>♪ And lay me up a pleasure ♪</i>

773
00:57:05,798 --> 00:57:12,572
<i>♪ Which will not rust
Nor wear away ♪</i>

774
00:57:15,241 --> 00:57:21,614
<i>♪ But dwell with me forever ♪</i>

775
00:57:21,714 --> 00:57:23,816
MAN: Reef topsail!

776
00:57:23,916 --> 00:57:26,352
MARY (VO): <i>Mother Ann
led the group in daily worship</i>

777
00:57:26,452 --> 00:57:27,553
<i>on the upper deck,</i>

778
00:57:27,653 --> 00:57:29,890
<i>despite the vexation and grouse</i>

779
00:57:29,990 --> 00:57:31,992
<i>of their fellow passengers
and crewmen.</i>

780
00:57:32,092 --> 00:57:33,359
Mother Ann, you must excuse me.

781
00:57:33,459 --> 00:57:34,394
I feel quite ill again
this morning.

782
00:57:34,494 --> 00:57:35,695
You're excused.

783
00:57:36,562 --> 00:57:38,464
(RETCHING)

784
00:57:40,333 --> 00:57:41,802
MARY: Four weeks, dear.

785
00:57:41,902 --> 00:57:43,569
If the skies stay kind to us.

786
00:57:44,871 --> 00:57:46,573
You must try
and keep some food down,

787
00:57:46,673 --> 00:57:47,574
or you will only
become more feeble.

788
00:57:47,674 --> 00:57:49,543
MAN: Take in fore topgallant!

789
00:57:53,714 --> 00:57:58,184
<i>♪ All is concert
All is summer ♪</i>

790
00:57:58,284 --> 00:58:02,723
<i>♪ All is concert
All is summer ♪</i>

791
00:58:02,823 --> 00:58:07,594
<i>♪ All is concert
All is summer ♪</i>

792
00:58:07,694 --> 00:58:09,796
<i>- ♪ All is concert ♪</i>
- Still your bone box, besom!

793
00:58:09,896 --> 00:58:12,065
<i>- ♪ All is summer ♪</i>
- Shut it, he said.

794
00:58:12,166 --> 00:58:14,368
<i>- ♪ All is concert ♪</i>
- Hokum!

795
00:58:14,468 --> 00:58:16,170
<i>- ♪ All is summer ♪</i>
- Quiet down!

796
00:58:16,270 --> 00:58:18,805
- Oi! Whooperups!
<i>- ♪ All is concert ♪</i>

797
00:58:18,905 --> 00:58:20,807
<i>- ♪ All is summer ♪</i>
- Shut up!

798
00:58:21,242 --> 00:58:23,410
<i>- ♪ All is concert ♪</i>
- Shut up!

799
00:58:23,510 --> 00:58:24,979
<i>- ♪ All is summer ♪</i>
- Shut up!

800
00:58:25,079 --> 00:58:28,682
- Don't sing!
<i>- ♪ All is concert, all is-- ♪</i>

801
00:58:28,782 --> 00:58:31,285
My dear brethren
and sisters, stop!

802
00:58:31,385 --> 00:58:32,619
(SINGING STOPS)

803
00:58:32,719 --> 00:58:35,156
We must pray for the seafarers.

804
00:58:35,522 --> 00:58:38,359
MAN: Shut your bone box, besom!

805
00:58:38,459 --> 00:58:42,129
Impoverished souls!
Adventitious sinners!

806
00:58:42,229 --> 00:58:44,098
These men know not
what they give tongue to.

807
00:58:44,198 --> 00:58:46,868
I know just what I say, missus.

808
00:58:46,968 --> 00:58:48,235
Shut it!

809
00:58:48,335 --> 00:58:50,472
These men know not what they do.

810
00:58:50,572 --> 00:58:52,840
- Stop!
- We must pray for them.

811
00:58:53,541 --> 00:58:54,942
<i>- ♪ All is concert ♪</i>
- Stop that!

812
00:58:55,042 --> 00:58:57,111
- Shut it, he said!
<i>- ♪ All is summer... ♪</i>

813
00:58:57,211 --> 00:58:58,846
Shut up!

814
00:58:58,946 --> 00:59:02,350
- Oi, whooperups! Quiet!
<i>- ♪ All is summer ♪</i>

815
00:59:02,450 --> 00:59:04,719
- Shut up!
<i>- ♪ All is concert ♪</i>

816
00:59:04,819 --> 00:59:07,255
(THUNDER BOOMING)

817
00:59:10,825 --> 00:59:12,427
SMITH: Take in topgallant!

818
00:59:12,860 --> 00:59:14,162
MAN: Take in topgallant!

819
00:59:14,997 --> 00:59:16,064
SMITH: Take in royal!

820
00:59:16,164 --> 00:59:17,499
(SHAKERS SINGING)

821
00:59:17,665 --> 00:59:20,402
I am ordering all clamorous
and disruptive noisemaking

822
00:59:20,502 --> 00:59:22,070
ceased without delay!

823
00:59:22,170 --> 00:59:23,972
- Captain, stop!
- You heard me.

824
00:59:24,072 --> 00:59:25,440
Halt where you are, Captain.

825
00:59:25,540 --> 00:59:27,810
We are in various states
of undress!

826
00:59:28,376 --> 00:59:30,345
If you do not stop the racket,

827
00:59:30,445 --> 00:59:32,014
I have vowed my crewmen

828
00:59:32,114 --> 00:59:34,717
to have all your disobedients
cast into the sea!

829
00:59:34,817 --> 00:59:36,284
- And I am earnest.
- We do fear God

830
00:59:36,384 --> 00:59:37,786
more than we fear Captain Smith

831
00:59:37,886 --> 00:59:40,989
and we shall
conduct our worship, as usual,

832
00:59:41,089 --> 00:59:43,058
with special orison
for seafaring sinners.

833
00:59:43,158 --> 00:59:45,327
And you, Captain,
we shall pray for you, as well.

834
00:59:45,427 --> 00:59:47,029
(LOUD CRASHING)

835
00:59:47,129 --> 00:59:49,197
ANN: Mary, take my hand!

836
00:59:49,297 --> 00:59:52,435
SMITH: (GRUNTS) Take refuge!
Sister Ann!

837
00:59:52,535 --> 00:59:54,403
Do not exit your cabins

838
00:59:54,503 --> 00:59:57,506
until you've received word
that it is safe to do so!

839
01:00:04,913 --> 01:00:07,283
MAN: Prepare to set
storm canvas!

840
01:00:07,383 --> 01:00:10,653
Lower broad sail!

841
01:00:12,989 --> 01:00:15,424
Don't go up there, miss!
You'll be sucked out to sea.

842
01:00:15,524 --> 01:00:17,526
The lot of you
should be pleased, then.

843
01:00:18,694 --> 01:00:20,729
(SHIP RUMBLING, CREAKING)

844
01:00:23,299 --> 01:00:25,134
(WOMAN WAILING)

845
01:00:25,234 --> 01:00:26,903
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

846
01:00:27,003 --> 01:00:28,037
Cunningham.

847
01:00:32,375 --> 01:00:33,342
Captain!

848
01:00:34,377 --> 01:00:35,111
Captain!

849
01:00:37,080 --> 01:00:39,015
SMITH: Prepare to cover
the hatches!

850
01:00:39,115 --> 01:00:40,484
MAN: Preparing!

851
01:00:40,984 --> 01:00:43,620
SMITH: A plank has been
struck loose at the keel.

852
01:00:43,720 --> 01:00:44,988
I have gone upstairs

853
01:00:45,088 --> 01:00:47,090
to look through the porthole
to the upper deck.

854
01:00:47,190 --> 01:00:48,858
There is no way to mend it.

855
01:00:48,958 --> 01:00:50,860
We must all perish
before morning.

856
01:00:50,960 --> 01:00:52,829
Be of good cheer, Captain!

857
01:00:52,929 --> 01:00:55,465
There shall not the hair
on our heads perish.

858
01:00:55,565 --> 01:00:57,301
We will arrive safely
in America.

859
01:00:57,401 --> 01:00:59,102
MARY (VO): <i>Ann explained
that she had seen</i>

860
01:00:59,203 --> 01:01:00,870
<i>two bright angels of God</i>

861
01:01:00,970 --> 01:01:02,506
<i>standing by the mast,</i>

862
01:01:02,606 --> 01:01:03,807
<i>through whom she received</i>

863
01:01:03,907 --> 01:01:06,110
<i>the promise
of their safe-passing.</i>

864
01:01:06,210 --> 01:01:09,279
I will call now on my companions
to assist your crewmen.

865
01:01:10,747 --> 01:01:11,615
MARY: Ann!

866
01:01:14,318 --> 01:01:15,953
(HULL CREAKING)

867
01:01:16,053 --> 01:01:18,088
(PEOPLE SHOUTING)

868
01:01:23,127 --> 01:01:25,996
MARY (VO): <i>Soon after,
a mighty wave struck the ship</i>

869
01:01:26,096 --> 01:01:27,865
<i>and pressed
the loose plank tight,</i>

870
01:01:27,965 --> 01:01:28,966
<i>stopping the leak.</i>

871
01:01:30,668 --> 01:01:33,538
<i>Shakers fervently helped
the sailors at the pumps,</i>

872
01:01:33,638 --> 01:01:36,941
<i>which, as the Captain noted,
had a miraculous effect.</i>

873
01:01:37,041 --> 01:01:38,843
(GROANING WITH EFFORT)

874
01:01:38,943 --> 01:01:41,912
<i>They were left to pray in peace
for the rest of the journey.</i>

875
01:01:42,012 --> 01:01:46,050
<i>♪ High over the billows
We are wafted along ♪</i>

876
01:01:46,150 --> 01:01:50,621
<i>♪ Angel wing carry us ♪</i>

877
01:01:50,721 --> 01:01:54,825
<i>♪ Not one ripple
To break on our song ♪</i>

878
01:01:55,260 --> 01:01:59,097
<i>♪ All is peace before us ♪</i>

879
01:01:59,530 --> 01:02:03,534
<i>♪ All is concert,
All is summer ♪</i>

880
01:02:03,634 --> 01:02:07,905
<i>♪ While to heaven
We are going ♪</i>

881
01:02:08,006 --> 01:02:12,277
<i>♪ But in the desert
We are leaving behind ♪</i>

882
01:02:12,377 --> 01:02:16,347
<i>♪ Wintry winds are blowing ♪</i>

883
01:02:17,015 --> 01:02:21,086
(MEN VOCALIZING)

884
01:02:34,466 --> 01:02:38,470
<i>♪ High over the billows
We are wafted along ♪</i>

885
