<i>♪ All is concert
All is summer ♪</i>

895
01:03:22,548 --> 01:03:26,619
<i>♪ All is concert
All is summer ♪</i>

896
01:03:26,719 --> 01:03:30,857
<i>♪ All is concert
All is summer ♪</i>

897
01:03:30,957 --> 01:03:35,261
<i>♪ All is concert
All is summer ♪</i>

898
01:03:35,362 --> 01:03:39,599
<i>♪ All is concert
All is summer ♪</i>

899
01:03:40,032 --> 01:03:43,936
<i>♪ All is concert
All is summer ♪</i>

900
01:03:44,036 --> 01:03:48,308
<i>♪ All is concert
All is summer ♪</i>

901
01:03:48,408 --> 01:03:52,745
<i>♪ All is concert
All is summer ♪</i>

902
01:03:52,845 --> 01:03:57,184
<i>♪ All is concert
All is summer ♪</i>

903
01:03:57,284 --> 01:04:01,454
<i>♪ All is concert
All is summer ♪</i>

904
01:04:01,554 --> 01:04:04,424
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

905
01:04:07,294 --> 01:04:10,163
(PANTING DEEPLY)

906
01:04:14,234 --> 01:04:16,003
(CATTLE LOWING)

907
01:04:21,474 --> 01:04:23,410
(BELLS CLANGING)

908
01:04:23,511 --> 01:04:25,412
(MEN SHOUTING)

909
01:04:26,179 --> 01:04:28,181
(HORSE WHINNIES)

910
01:04:28,281 --> 01:04:30,684
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

911
01:04:30,784 --> 01:04:32,252
(WHISPERING)
Cunningham. Cunningham.

912
01:04:52,473 --> 01:04:55,109
AUCTIONEER: I'm gonna start
the bidding at 150.

913
01:04:55,209 --> 01:04:56,844
There's no need to waste time.

914
01:04:56,945 --> 01:04:58,612
He's the pick of the herd, gentlemen.

915
01:04:58,712 --> 01:05:00,481
You won't find his like

916
01:05:00,581 --> 01:05:02,583
- in these degenerate days.
- Are they selling them?

917
01:05:02,683 --> 01:05:04,252
AUCTIONEER: Who'll give me 150?

918
01:05:05,954 --> 01:05:07,555
Sinful as it is
incomprehensible.

919
01:05:07,655 --> 01:05:09,824
- MAN: 160!
- AUCTIONEER: 170!

920
01:05:09,924 --> 01:05:11,893
Every man, woman, and child
is a child of God.

921
01:05:11,993 --> 01:05:13,094
MAN 2: 170.

922
01:05:14,162 --> 01:05:17,165
Mother Ann, the women are tired.

923
01:05:17,265 --> 01:05:19,067
Should I look into a bed stay
for the evening?

924
01:05:19,167 --> 01:05:21,402
That's a terrible waste
of your resources, Mr. Hocknell.

925
01:05:21,503 --> 01:05:22,771
Please hold on to your notecase.

926
01:05:22,871 --> 01:05:24,573
- These men are without disease.
- Shame!

927
01:05:24,673 --> 01:05:26,441
- Shame!
- Shame!

928
01:05:26,541 --> 01:05:27,576
- JOHN: Shame!
- WILLIAM: Shame!

929
01:05:27,676 --> 01:05:28,910
- Shame!
- Shame!

930
01:05:29,010 --> 01:05:30,044
- Shame!
- Shame!

931
01:05:35,083 --> 01:05:37,619
MARY (VO): <i>On that hot
August afternoon,</i>

932
01:05:37,719 --> 01:05:39,521
<i>the Shakers went in search</i>

933
01:05:39,621 --> 01:05:42,224
<i>of a wide avenue
called Broad Street,</i>

934
01:05:42,324 --> 01:05:44,893
<i>where Mother Ann felt confident
she would discover</i>

935
01:05:44,993 --> 01:05:46,628
<i>what her vision had revealed.</i>

936
01:05:57,172 --> 01:05:59,041
Pardon me, are you the mistress
of this house?

937
01:05:59,141 --> 01:06:00,409
WOMAN: I am.

938
01:06:00,509 --> 01:06:01,676
Mrs. Cunningham?

939
01:06:04,279 --> 01:06:06,749
You'll have to please excuse me,
I've just stepped outside

940
01:06:06,849 --> 01:06:08,083
to escape the heat, you see.

941
01:06:09,051 --> 01:06:10,185
Have we made acquaintance?

942
01:06:10,285 --> 01:06:11,987
I am commissioned
by the Almighty God

943
01:06:12,087 --> 01:06:14,389
to preach the everlasting gospel
to America.

944
01:06:14,924 --> 01:06:18,360
And an angel commanded me,
here, to this house,

945
01:06:18,461 --> 01:06:20,329
to make a home for me
and my people.

946
01:06:20,830 --> 01:06:23,433
She said the name, Cunningham.

947
01:06:23,533 --> 01:06:25,835
MARY (VO): <i>Mrs. Cunningham was
a simple-minded woman</i>

948
01:06:25,935 --> 01:06:27,503
<i>who recently faced
financial hardship...</i>

949
01:06:27,603 --> 01:06:28,971
I see.

950
01:06:29,071 --> 01:06:31,073
<i>...and began offering
affordable accommodations</i>

951
01:06:31,173 --> 01:06:31,907
<i>in her home.</i>

952
01:06:33,509 --> 01:06:35,978
<i>Although she didn't possess
deep faith,</i>

953
01:06:36,078 --> 01:06:39,115
<i>she had a great curiosity
about the world.</i>

954
01:06:39,949 --> 01:06:42,185
<i>She felt privileged
to have been chosen</i>

955
01:06:42,285 --> 01:06:44,287
<i>by a higher force,</i>

956
01:06:44,387 --> 01:06:47,623
<i>which motivated her
to provide discounted rates</i>

957
01:06:47,723 --> 01:06:50,626
<i>along with a warm welcome
to her guests.</i>

958
01:06:50,726 --> 01:06:56,599
(INAUDIBLE CHATTER)

959
01:07:22,959 --> 01:07:24,795
(SILVERWARE CLATTERING)

960
01:07:24,895 --> 01:07:26,597
May I please be excused,
Mother Ann?

961
01:07:26,697 --> 01:07:28,098
You may, Nancy.

962
01:07:28,332 --> 01:07:31,935
Our privy is located just
outside across the vestibule.

963
01:07:32,035 --> 01:07:33,103
You'll see a doorway
to exit through

964
01:07:33,204 --> 01:07:34,605
at the far end
of the corridor.

965
01:07:34,705 --> 01:07:36,073
Thank you kindly,
Mrs. Cunningham.

966
01:07:48,685 --> 01:07:50,354
If you'll please excuse me,
as well.

967
01:07:50,454 --> 01:07:52,523
I'll step out front
for some fresh air.

968
01:07:52,623 --> 01:07:54,992
My equilibrium thinks me
still aboard the <i>Mariah.</i>

969
01:07:57,561 --> 01:07:59,697
(LIGHT CHATTER, LAUGHTER)

970
01:08:04,135 --> 01:08:06,538
(MOANING SOFTLY)

971
01:08:08,405 --> 01:08:09,541
I haven't washed.

972
01:08:09,641 --> 01:08:10,875
The night of the tempest,

973
01:08:10,975 --> 01:08:12,744
I thought I mightn't ever
see you again.

974
01:08:15,580 --> 01:08:17,449
We mustn't waste another moment.

975
01:08:20,952 --> 01:08:22,186
We mustn't.

976
01:08:22,287 --> 01:08:25,657
(BOTH GASP, PANTING)

977
01:08:25,757 --> 01:08:28,360
The men among us shall stay
only a fortnight.

978
01:08:28,460 --> 01:08:29,894
James Whittaker, William,

979
01:08:29,994 --> 01:08:32,197
my son, Richard,
and I must leave,

980
01:08:32,297 --> 01:08:35,100
in search of a suitable piece
of land up the Hudson

981
01:08:35,200 --> 01:08:36,768
on which for us to settle.

982
01:08:36,868 --> 01:08:39,271
Have you a boatman arranged
for your journey upriver?

983
01:08:40,973 --> 01:08:43,008
JOHN: Is there someone
you might suggest?

984
01:08:43,641 --> 01:08:47,212
I'm closely familiar
with a Dutchman, a hunter,

985
01:08:47,813 --> 01:08:49,681
who's well acquainted
with those macabre customs

986
01:08:49,782 --> 01:08:51,416
of the wild people.

987
01:08:51,516 --> 01:08:52,751
Wild people?

988
01:08:53,518 --> 01:08:55,087
River Injuns.

989
01:08:55,688 --> 01:08:57,522
And to go from New York
to Albany,

990
01:08:57,623 --> 01:09:00,959
you consult not a timetable
but a calendar.

991
01:09:01,393 --> 01:09:03,228
So, in mild weather,
you take a boat,

992
01:09:03,328 --> 01:09:05,964
but when the Hudson is frozen,
it's a stagecoach.

993
01:09:06,064 --> 01:09:08,434
Either way,
it is a three-day trip.

994
01:09:10,035 --> 01:09:11,737
And you, Standerin?

995
01:09:11,837 --> 01:09:14,373
Will you be going along, too,
with the others?

996
01:09:15,107 --> 01:09:18,477
I, uh, plan to stay behind,
seek work here in town,

997
01:09:18,577 --> 01:09:20,346
aid in the support
of our mission.

998
01:09:21,146 --> 01:09:23,182
JOHN: Accompany me
to the forge tomorrow.

999
01:09:23,782 --> 01:09:26,285
We'll see if there are gaps
which need filling.

1000
01:09:26,385 --> 01:09:28,187
Abraham is a remarkable farrier.

1001
01:09:35,728 --> 01:09:37,430
JOHN: Where has that boy of mine
gone to?

1002
01:09:38,464 --> 01:09:39,999
Pardon me, will you?

1003
01:09:40,099 --> 01:09:41,968
Discourtesy is so unlike him.

1004
01:09:43,769 --> 01:09:46,840
Seems like his breadbasket
is all tied up in knots.

1005
01:09:46,940 --> 01:09:48,875
(LIGHT LAUGHTER)

1006
01:09:50,677 --> 01:09:51,711
JOHN: Richard!

1007
01:10:05,191 --> 01:10:06,726
- (RICHARD AND NANCY PANTING)
- (DISGUSTED GROAN)

1008
01:10:06,826 --> 01:10:08,194
God in Heaven!

1009
01:10:08,294 --> 01:10:09,663
(PANTING CONTINUES)

1010
01:10:14,834 --> 01:10:16,703
They are not willing to forsake.

1011
01:10:16,803 --> 01:10:18,004
They plan to marry.

1012
01:10:20,707 --> 01:10:22,142
Then they must leave us.

1013
01:10:33,520 --> 01:10:35,122
Is their love so sinful?

1014
01:10:36,590 --> 01:10:38,558
No, 'tis a thing of beauty.

1015
01:10:39,894 --> 01:10:42,462
They can love each other deeply,
like I love you.

1016
01:10:43,430 --> 01:10:45,199
They...

1017
01:10:45,299 --> 01:10:48,102
The love they have chosen
will not last.

1018
01:10:49,169 --> 01:10:53,608
It will turn your body into
a senseless, unsavory corpse.

1019
01:10:53,708 --> 01:10:55,976
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

1020
01:10:56,076 --> 01:10:59,379
The desire of the flesh
will fester and tear it apart.

1021
01:11:00,848 --> 01:11:03,384
And that desire is
an ugly beast.

1022
01:11:03,484 --> 01:11:07,455
And that beast destroys
all that is beautiful and pure.

1023
01:11:10,758 --> 01:11:13,394
Both of us have suffered
on our journey.

1024
01:11:14,629 --> 01:11:16,831
We have made
tremendous sacrifices

1025
01:11:16,931 --> 01:11:21,102
to receive the greatest love
that one can experience,

1026
01:11:21,202 --> 01:11:23,271
and to give it entirely.

1027
01:11:29,410 --> 01:11:31,246
It pains me to see her go.

1028
01:11:33,514 --> 01:11:35,750
I would force her to stay
and send him away.

1029
01:11:35,851 --> 01:11:37,518
She was left in our care,
after all.

1030
01:11:37,618 --> 01:11:39,120
But that we cannot, William.

1031
01:11:40,388 --> 01:11:42,858
She must choose
our way of life freely.

1032
01:11:43,959 --> 01:11:46,161
(ANN SNIFFLES)

1033
01:11:46,261 --> 01:11:49,230
(MEN AND WOMEN
VOCALIZING SOFTLY)

1034
01:11:49,330 --> 01:11:50,799
(ANN WHIMPERS LIGHTLY)

1035
01:12:04,145 --> 01:12:05,381
(DOOR THUDS GENTLY)

1036
01:12:05,481 --> 01:12:07,349
(HORSE NICKERING)

1037
01:12:21,230 --> 01:12:23,232
MARY (VO): <i>Regretful
and ashamed,</i>

1038
01:12:23,332 --> 01:12:27,369
<i>Hocknell's son, Richard,
and Ann's niece, Nancy,</i>

1039
01:12:27,469 --> 01:12:31,273
<i>were exigently forced to leave
their family and friends behind</i>

1040
01:12:31,373 --> 01:12:33,609
<i>without pageantry of farewell.</i>

1041
01:12:36,012 --> 01:12:37,814
- (WHIP SNAPS)
- (HORSE WHINNIES)

1042
01:12:40,817 --> 01:12:42,619
<i>Eight became six.</i>

1043
01:13:02,539 --> 01:13:04,641
(BIRDS CALLING IN DISTANCE)

1044
01:13:10,046 --> 01:13:12,048
Slept like wee babes,
did you, lads?

1045
01:13:12,582 --> 01:13:14,384
As well as one might on a raft.

1046
01:13:18,555 --> 01:13:20,257
Didn't Cunningham say
he was Dutch?

1047
01:13:21,258 --> 01:13:22,659
He's a Dutchman.

1048
01:13:22,759 --> 01:13:24,794
DUTCHMAN:
Beautiful morning now, I say.

1049
01:13:24,895 --> 01:13:27,097
But again,
all white geese are swans.

1050
01:13:30,968 --> 01:13:34,237
MARY (VO): <i>To the great
frustration of the Irishman,</i>

1051
01:13:34,337 --> 01:13:36,106
<i>the men journeyed upstream</i>

1052
01:13:36,206 --> 01:13:40,010
<i>without a clear itinerary
or navigational aids,</i>

1053
01:13:40,110 --> 01:13:43,313
<i>relying solely
on Mr. Hocknell's instincts.</i>

1054
01:13:50,253 --> 01:13:52,523
(BIRDS TWITTERING)

1055
01:13:54,057 --> 01:13:55,793
DUTCHMAN: It's been two days,
Mr. Hocknell.

1056
01:13:55,893 --> 01:13:58,329
Nothing seems to stir
your imagination.

1057
01:13:58,429 --> 01:14:01,031
JOHN: It is not me imagination.

1058
01:14:01,131 --> 01:14:06,204
It is me Divine inspiration
that is leading us.

1059
01:14:06,304 --> 01:14:08,939
MARY (VO): <i>The night before
their expedition,</i>

1060
01:14:09,039 --> 01:14:12,610
<i>Brother Hocknell had shared
a vivid dream with the men,</i>

1061
01:14:13,177 --> 01:14:17,281
<i>featuring an expansive field
with tall grass,</i>

1062
01:14:17,381 --> 01:14:20,985
<i>bordered by 12 large oak trees.</i>

1063
01:14:21,085 --> 01:14:23,922
<i>They all believed
this was the ideal place</i>

1064
01:14:24,022 --> 01:14:25,389
<i>for them to settle.</i>

1065
01:14:26,224 --> 01:14:29,027
These are the wild people

1066
01:14:29,127 --> 01:14:31,796
we have compensated you
to protect us from?

1067
01:14:31,896 --> 01:14:33,732
DUTCHMAN: The women
and children, yes.

1068
01:14:34,232 --> 01:14:35,1000
The manful redskin, yet.

1069
01:14:37,669 --> 01:14:40,271
You've never lain your eye
on a more wretched brute.

1070
01:14:44,843 --> 01:14:48,680
(JOHN MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY)

1071
01:14:54,185 --> 01:14:55,820
Your friend's a bit mad, is he?

1072
01:14:56,255 --> 01:14:57,956
He doesn't help us to cook
or make camp.

1073
01:15:00,559 --> 01:15:02,827
I'm not mad,
but perhaps

1074
01:15:02,927 --> 01:15:05,063
I've become indolent
in my old age.

1075
01:15:05,164 --> 01:15:06,965
I'm not cheap, however,

1076
01:15:07,066 --> 01:15:10,369
so I've afforded myself
the opportunity to do nothing.

1077
01:15:10,469 --> 01:15:14,139
May I pray now to
the Almighty God in some peace?

1078
01:15:19,444 --> 01:15:22,214
I'm sorry, Lord,
I could not control my temper.

1079
01:15:23,582 --> 01:15:26,018
And it is something
I have been working on.

1080
01:15:27,920 --> 01:15:30,389
I should not have lashed out
at this common man

1081
01:15:30,489 --> 01:15:33,759
who does not understand
the path that we're on,

1082
01:15:33,859 --> 01:15:36,261
who cannot comprehend in any way

1083
01:15:36,361 --> 01:15:38,631
the kind of endurance

1084
01:15:38,731 --> 01:15:41,266
that is required
to make this journey.

1085
01:15:43,403 --> 01:15:46,872
I weakened at a point
when I should have been strong,

1086
01:15:46,972 --> 01:15:49,842
and I really beg you
for forgiveness.

1087
01:15:49,942 --> 01:15:52,412
And I will apologize
to this man,

1088
01:15:52,512 --> 01:15:54,514
although he does
get under my skin

1089
01:15:54,614 --> 01:15:57,583
with his pettiness
and his small-mindedness.

1090
01:15:57,683 --> 01:16:01,287
But I should rise above that.
I should know better.

1091
01:16:01,687 --> 01:16:04,524
I sit in endless gratitude

1092
01:16:04,624 --> 01:16:07,160
for all the gifts
that you've given me...

1093
01:16:07,260 --> 01:16:09,529
DUTCHMAN: Did you sleep a wink,
Mr. Hocknell?

1094
01:16:09,629 --> 01:16:11,397
...that you are constantly
bestowing upon me.

1095
01:16:22,809 --> 01:16:24,377
MARY (VO): <i>Legend has it,</i>

1096
01:16:24,477 --> 01:16:27,013
<i>that on the third day
of the men's search,</i>

1097
01:16:27,113 --> 01:16:29,816
<i>a most peculiar thing happened.</i>

1098
01:16:30,884 --> 01:16:31,985
Brother Hocknell?

1099
01:16:33,720 --> 01:16:34,721
Brother Hocknell?

1100
01:16:39,693 --> 01:16:41,695
<i>♪ I am searching
I am led ♪</i>

1101
01:16:44,465 --> 01:16:46,600
WILLIAM: <i>* He is searching
He is led ♪</i>

1102
01:16:49,135 --> 01:16:51,638
JOHN: <i>* I am searching
I am led ♪</i>

1103
01:16:53,874 --> 01:16:56,042
WILLIAM: <i>* He is searching
He is led ♪</i>

1104
01:16:58,212 --> 01:17:00,247
JOHN: <i>* What eyes reveal ♪</i>

1105
01:17:00,347 --> 01:17:02,949
<i>♪ It's our ideal ♪</i>

1106
01:17:03,050 --> 01:17:06,520
BOTH: <i>* That our ordeal
Is worth it ♪</i>

1107
01:17:12,726 --> 01:17:14,962
<i>♪ I am searching
I am led ♪</i>

1108
01:17:17,298 --> 01:17:19,433
<i>♪ He is searching
He is led ♪</i>

1109
01:17:21,836 --> 01:17:24,672
<i>♪ I am searching
I am led ♪</i>

1110
01:17:26,841 --> 01:17:29,343
<i>♪ He is searching
He is led ♪</i>

1111
01:17:31,178 --> 01:17:33,280
JOHN: <i>* What eyes reveal ♪</i>

1112
01:17:33,380 --> 01:17:35,617
<i>♪ It's our ideal ♪</i>

1113
01:17:35,983 --> 01:17:39,787
BOTH: <i>* That our ordeal
Is worth it ♪</i>

1114
01:17:39,887 --> 01:17:40,922
DUTCHMAN: Brother Hocknell!

1115
01:17:41,022 --> 01:17:42,590
JOHN: <i>* What eyes reveal ♪</i>

1116
01:17:42,690 --> 01:17:45,293
<i>♪ It's our ideal ♪</i>

1117
01:17:45,393 --> 01:17:48,863
<i>♪ That our ordeal is worth it ♪</i>

1118
01:17:50,097 --> 01:17:52,667
<i>♪ Oh, God, I saw it ♪</i>

1119
01:17:52,767 --> 01:17:55,036
<i>♪ Like through a glass ♪</i>

1120
01:17:55,137 --> 01:17:57,739
<i>♪ My visions shall ♪</i>

1121
01:17:57,839 --> 01:18:02,744
<i>♪ Come to pass ♪</i>

1122
01:18:02,844 --> 01:18:05,247
<i>♪ Pass ♪</i>

1123
01:18:05,347 --> 01:18:11,353
ALL: <i>* Pass ♪</i>

1124
01:18:21,630 --> 01:18:22,965
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

1125
01:18:23,065 --> 01:18:25,300
(BIRDS TWITTERING)

1126
01:18:30,305 --> 01:18:31,807
(FOOTSTEPS)

1127
01:18:41,517 --> 01:18:43,018
(LIQUID SLOSHING)

1128
01:18:46,189 --> 01:18:48,891
(WHISPERS) Brother Abraham,
is something the matter?

1129
01:18:48,991 --> 01:18:51,794
ABRAHAM: I need to speak
with her in private.

1130
01:18:51,894 --> 01:18:55,598
- Brother?
- Sister, go and take my bed.

1131
01:18:55,698 --> 01:18:57,100
The men are away now.

1132
01:18:57,967 --> 01:19:00,403
Please, just leave me
in peace with her.

1133
01:19:02,338 --> 01:19:04,173
(FEET SHUFFLING)

1134
01:19:12,048 --> 01:19:13,950
(DOGS BARK IN DISTANCE)

1135
01:19:24,528 --> 01:19:25,795
- (ANN GASPS)
- Mother,

1136
01:19:25,895 --> 01:19:27,764
I've endured your sensual
abstinence for six years...

1137
01:19:27,864 --> 01:19:29,098
(WHISPERS) You are setting
a terrible precedent.

1138
01:19:29,198 --> 01:19:30,834
No, you will not
talk over me!

1139
01:19:30,934 --> 01:19:32,469
Quiet your voice!

1140
01:19:32,569 --> 01:19:36,906
(SIGHS)
I will give you a chance now

1141
01:19:37,006 --> 01:19:39,976
to rectify your standing
in my eyes.

1142
01:19:40,076 --> 01:19:43,547
Go to bed with me, dutifully,
as you once promised.

1143
01:19:43,647 --> 01:19:45,182
No one can reach God

1144
01:19:45,282 --> 01:19:46,550
while wallowing
in the lust of the flesh.

1145
01:19:46,650 --> 01:19:48,652
Oh, enough!

1146
01:19:48,752 --> 01:19:50,587
I want to please
my husband, I do.

1147
01:19:51,588 --> 01:19:53,123
But I cannot.

1148
01:19:53,823 --> 01:19:56,226
My natural instincts
have died away in love of God.

1149
01:19:58,963 --> 01:20:01,065
I urge you to renounce
your testimony...

1150
01:20:03,067 --> 01:20:07,337
and live in sexual cohabitation
like the rest of the world.

1151
01:20:07,437 --> 01:20:09,539
Abraham, the exuberant bliss
of Christ--

1152
01:20:09,639 --> 01:20:10,675
ABRAHAM:
No. And the more you talk of

1153
01:20:10,775 --> 01:20:12,576
"exuberant bliss
of Divine intercourse,"

1154
01:20:12,677 --> 01:20:16,947
the more I shall drink, and
not stop myself until I am dead.

1155
01:20:20,851 --> 01:20:23,988
- (DOGS BARKING)
- (WIND BLOWING)

1156
01:20:27,191 --> 01:20:29,627
Do those that follow thou

1157
01:20:29,727 --> 01:20:32,363
and abide ye's every locution,

1158
01:20:32,463 --> 01:20:34,465
know their Mother Ann
to be illiterate?

1159
01:20:37,435 --> 01:20:38,669
Tell me...

1160
01:20:39,404 --> 01:20:41,572
how does one contribute
to the scripture

1161
01:20:42,173 --> 01:20:44,442
if thou cannot stable a quill?

1162
01:20:49,214 --> 01:20:51,149
I've kept your secrets, Ann Lee.

1163
01:20:52,850 --> 01:20:54,452
And you will keep mine.

1164
01:20:57,555 --> 01:21:00,725
(FOOTSTEPS RECEDING)

1165
01:21:05,030 --> 01:21:08,399
(DOOR SHUTS)

1166
01:21:15,607 --> 01:21:19,277
(PANTING)

1167
01:21:21,547 --> 01:21:24,716
(DOOR THUDDING)

1168
01:21:27,386 --> 01:21:28,887
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

1169
01:21:28,987 --> 01:21:31,089
ABRAHAM:
So you are to be my wife now.

1170
01:21:32,558 --> 01:21:34,025
Go to the room. Now.

1171
01:21:36,662 --> 01:21:41,033
Now, if you do not consent
to sexual cohabitation with me,

1172
01:21:41,133 --> 01:21:42,868
I will take this woman
for my wife.

1173
01:21:42,968 --> 01:21:44,836
I will not do it,
if you should take my life

1174
01:21:44,936 --> 01:21:46,172
as consequence for my refusal.

1175
01:21:46,272 --> 01:21:47,639
(PANTING)

1176
01:21:47,739 --> 01:21:49,675
I'll do anything for my husband

1177
01:21:49,775 --> 01:21:53,012
which justice, reason,
and humanity requires,

1178
01:21:53,112 --> 01:21:55,647
but I do not consent
to violate my duty to God.

1179
01:21:57,116 --> 01:21:59,051
And I will endeavor
to prevail on you

1180
01:21:59,151 --> 01:22:01,821
to return to your duty
and be faithful.

1181
01:22:02,488 --> 01:22:04,156
(SHOUTING)

1182
01:22:04,256 --> 01:22:06,092
Don't! Be quiet!

1183
01:22:06,192 --> 01:22:07,627
- (SHOUTS)
- Shh.

1184
01:22:07,727 --> 01:22:09,929
I solemnly vow
I shan't utter another word

1185
01:22:10,029 --> 01:22:11,430
if you just lower your voice.

1186
01:22:12,465 --> 01:22:13,633
Lower your voice.

1187
01:22:14,601 --> 01:22:15,768
I will listen.

1188
01:22:16,803 --> 01:22:18,304
Shhhh.

1189
01:22:19,171 --> 01:22:21,007
(BOTH PANTING)

1190
01:22:24,977 --> 01:22:26,246
You have been paid.

1191
01:22:29,549 --> 01:22:31,151
You are to be my wife now.

1192
01:22:34,554 --> 01:22:37,990
Come. Good.
Now, take me in your mouth.

1193
01:22:38,091 --> 01:22:39,826
(GASPS)

1194
01:22:41,428 --> 01:22:43,496
Now you-you are my wife now.

1195
01:22:45,298 --> 01:22:47,267
Go on. There.

1196
01:22:47,367 --> 01:22:49,136
(PANTING)

1197
01:22:49,236 --> 01:22:52,139
MARY (VO): <i>During
that long, bitter winter,</i>

1198
01:22:52,973 --> 01:22:55,909
<i>Mother Ann endured
deep sorrow of the soul.</i>

1199
01:22:57,978 --> 01:23:00,013
<i>Her children were dead.</i>

1200
01:23:00,113 --> 01:23:02,315
<i>Her husband had left her.</i>

1201
01:23:03,784 --> 01:23:06,286
<i>Her mission to America
seemed doomed.</i>

1202
01:23:06,386 --> 01:23:09,657
(RHYTHMIC BREATHING)

1203
01:23:23,471 --> 01:23:26,073
<i>But, with the arrival
of spring,</i>

1204
01:23:27,074 --> 01:23:29,042
<i>came news from the men</i>

1205
01:23:29,143 --> 01:23:31,979
<i>that it was time for
the women to journey upriver</i>

1206
01:23:32,080 --> 01:23:33,881
<i>and reunite
with their brothers.</i>

1207
01:23:46,995 --> 01:23:49,931
JOHN: From here, as far
as the eye can see, Mother,

1208
01:23:50,965 --> 01:23:51,933
it is ours.

1209
01:23:52,934 --> 01:23:54,368
The deed is done.

1210
01:23:56,971 --> 01:23:58,139
Brother Hocknell...

1211
01:23:59,641 --> 01:24:00,875
Tell it, brother.

1212
01:24:01,509 --> 01:24:04,445
How is anyone meant to find us
camouflaged by the pines?

1213
01:24:05,847 --> 01:24:08,717
My dear children. Hold fast.

1214
01:24:08,817 --> 01:24:10,719
Be not discouraged.

1215
01:24:10,819 --> 01:24:13,021
God has not sent us
to this land in vain.

1216
01:24:13,121 --> 01:24:16,625
He sent us to bring the Gospel
to this nation,

1217
01:24:17,225 --> 01:24:19,561
which is deeply lost in sin.

1218
01:24:20,161 --> 01:24:22,164
And there are a great number
who will embrace it.

1219
01:24:23,064 --> 01:24:24,933
And the time draws nigh.

1220
01:24:25,967 --> 01:24:28,470
Do you truly believe the Gospel
will open to the world?

1221
01:24:28,570 --> 01:24:30,639
Yea, Brother William.

1222
01:24:30,739 --> 01:24:32,407
I certainly know it will.

1223
01:24:33,175 --> 01:24:36,912
And the time is near at hand
when they will come like doves.

1224
01:24:39,148 --> 01:24:40,782
Mother, you have often
told us so, but...

1225
01:24:42,317 --> 01:24:43,652
they do not come.

1226
01:24:45,955 --> 01:24:49,124
We are so few,
yet we have lost so many.

1227
01:24:49,224 --> 01:24:51,160
Brother William,
you will go out and preach

1228
01:24:51,260 --> 01:24:52,895
and make our presence known.

1229
01:24:52,995 --> 01:24:54,429
Be patient.

1230
01:24:54,529 --> 01:24:57,600
Be patient, my dear children.

1231
01:24:57,700 --> 01:25:00,202
For I have seen
a great number coming now.

1232
01:25:01,136 --> 01:25:03,873
And you will soon see them
coming in great numbers.

1233
01:25:05,775 --> 01:25:07,076
I know it.

1234
01:25:10,413 --> 01:25:12,715
MARY (VO):
<i>After securing the land,</i>

1235
01:25:12,815 --> 01:25:15,285
<i>Brother Hocknell
had but enough capital left</i>

1236
01:25:15,385 --> 01:25:16,986
<i>to hire help to till it.</i>

1237
01:25:18,221 --> 01:25:20,256
<i>Yet Mother Ann
was eager to welcome</i>

1238
01:25:20,356 --> 01:25:21,891
<i>the farmers to the faith</i>

1239
01:25:21,991 --> 01:25:24,660
<i>and would not rest
until each one had joined.</i>

1240
01:25:47,350 --> 01:25:50,186
MARY (VO): <i>Soon thereafter,
Mother Ann sent Brother William</i>

1241
01:25:50,286 --> 01:25:52,288
<i>on a quest for new followers.</i>

1242
01:26:10,106 --> 01:26:13,844
(BIRDS CALLING)

1243
01:26:16,980 --> 01:26:20,951
<i>On the 19th of May,
in the year 1780,</i>

1244
01:26:21,052 --> 01:26:23,887
<i>the sky turned a strange hue.</i>

1245
01:26:23,988 --> 01:26:27,391
<i>William had heard tale
of a small godly lot,</i>

1246
01:26:27,491 --> 01:26:29,760
<i>who were certain
Judgment Day were nigh.</i>

1247
01:26:31,495 --> 01:26:36,467
PASTOR: Let it touch
your skin like silk or fire.

1248
01:26:36,567 --> 01:26:41,538
Now, each and every thing shall
be raised to life before God.

1249
01:26:41,638 --> 01:26:42,907
May he be praised...

1250
01:26:54,385 --> 01:26:59,457
Fear not,
the day of Resurrection is here.

1251
01:26:59,557 --> 01:27:04,161
Look up to God
at the first rays of the sun.

1252
01:27:04,261 --> 01:27:09,100
Let it touch your skin
like silk or fire.

1253
01:27:09,201 --> 01:27:11,969
Look up! Look up! Look up!

1254
01:27:12,537 --> 01:27:13,638
Fear not!

1255
01:27:13,738 --> 01:27:15,039
(WOMEN SCREAMING)

1256
01:27:15,140 --> 01:27:17,209
PASTOR:
Now, here it is, without delay!

1257
01:27:17,309 --> 01:27:20,912
At last! At last! At last!

1258
01:27:21,013 --> 01:27:24,649
- (WOMEN SCREAMING)
- (CRYING)

1259
01:27:24,749 --> 01:27:26,418
- You lied to us.
- What does it mean, Father?

1260
01:27:26,518 --> 01:27:28,854
- (PEOPLE SHOUTING)
- Hold your words, please!

1261
01:27:28,954 --> 01:27:31,356
Everyone, hold your words.

1262
01:27:31,456 --> 01:27:34,192
There were countless signs!
All led here.

1263
01:27:34,993 --> 01:27:36,428
What have I missed?

1264
01:27:36,862 --> 01:27:38,263
(SLAPS BOOK ON TABLE)

1265
01:27:38,897 --> 01:27:41,099
Are my calculations mistaken?

1266
01:27:41,533 --> 01:27:44,469
Or perhaps the Lord
hath taken pity on us all.

1267
01:27:45,037 --> 01:27:47,706
Father, could it be that
the cataclysm of your sermon--

1268
01:27:47,806 --> 01:27:51,009
Make no words,
Deacon Talmadge Bishop.

1269
01:27:52,044 --> 01:27:55,047
I require consultation
from our neighboring parishes.

1270
01:27:55,147 --> 01:27:58,617
I must journey to them at once
and collect their insights.

1271
01:27:59,184 --> 01:28:01,987
Your neighboring ministers
are of ill repute, Father.

1272
01:28:09,195 --> 01:28:13,432
St. Paul says it is no sin
for women to speak in churches.

1273
01:28:13,999 --> 01:28:17,503
Though I remain dubious,
I am drawn to hear her speak.

1274
01:28:17,603 --> 01:28:18,972
All that I have told you
is true,

1275
01:28:19,072 --> 01:28:20,639
but I advise you
to go for yourself,

1276
01:28:20,739 --> 01:28:22,141
and speak to Mother Ann.

1277
01:28:23,943 --> 01:28:25,845
MARY (VO):
<i>The news of religious liberty</i>

1278
01:28:25,945 --> 01:28:28,014
<i>stirred up many a sect
in America.</i>

1279
01:28:28,114 --> 01:28:31,117
<i>Most preaching doom
before paradise.</i>

1280
01:28:32,118 --> 01:28:36,756
<i>But Ann's word, paradise
through toil and chastity,</i>

1281
01:28:37,290 --> 01:28:39,626
<i>were a far simpler promise
to fulfill.</i>

1282
01:28:39,726 --> 01:28:41,460
(RHYTHMIC BREATHING)

1283
01:28:41,561 --> 01:28:46,232
<i>♪ Bow down, O Zion ♪</i>

1284
01:28:46,332 --> 01:28:50,003
<i>♪ And pray unto Heaven ♪</i>

1285
01:28:51,070 --> 01:28:55,108
<i>♪ That God in His mercy ♪</i>

1286
01:28:55,208 --> 01:28:58,445
<i>♪ Return unto thee ♪</i>

1287
01:28:59,979 --> 01:29:02,949
CONGREGATION: <i>* For thee
For, for thee ♪</i>

1288
01:29:04,451 --> 01:29:07,187
<i>♪ For thee
For, for thee ♪</i>

1289
01:29:07,287 --> 01:29:09,889
We have labored for years
in the work of the regeneration,

1290
01:29:09,989 --> 01:29:13,427
and have risen with Christ.

1291
01:29:13,527 --> 01:29:15,963
We have traveled with him
in the resurrection.

1292
01:29:16,063 --> 01:29:19,333
- <i>♪ That God in His mercy ♪</i>
- For the light and power of God

1293
01:29:19,433 --> 01:29:21,836
was revealed to our Mother Ann,
and through her,

1294
01:29:21,936 --> 01:29:24,538
reveals to those
who receive her testimony.

1295
01:29:24,638 --> 01:29:29,009
Such sensible effect in
giving them power over all sin.

1296
01:29:29,109 --> 01:29:32,112
<i>♪ For thee
For, for thee ♪</i>

1297
01:29:32,212 --> 01:29:37,184
- <i>♪ O, fall on the rock ♪</i>
- ALL: * <i>Rock ♪</i>

1298
01:29:38,185 --> 01:29:41,889
<i>♪ Each one and be broken ♪</i>

1299
01:29:43,123 --> 01:29:46,026
<i>♪ Mother's devotion ♪</i>

1300
01:29:47,127 --> 01:29:49,664
<i>♪ To set us all free ♪</i>

1301
01:29:49,764 --> 01:29:52,066
Revelations and gifts of God

1302
01:29:52,166 --> 01:29:56,103
that she was received
and acknowledged

1303
01:29:56,204 --> 01:30:00,040
- as the first spiritual leader!
- <i>♪ Fall on the rock ♪</i>

1304
01:30:00,741 --> 01:30:04,412
<i>♪ Each one and be broken ♪</i>

1305
01:30:05,646 --> 01:30:08,783
<i>- ♪ Mother's devotion ♪</i>
- (WAILING)

1306
01:30:09,650 --> 01:30:13,221
<i>♪ To set you all free ♪</i>

1307
01:30:13,321 --> 01:30:16,024
We are located
just a mere ten miles north.

1308
01:30:16,892 --> 01:30:20,595
<i>♪ Mother's devotion ♪</i>

1309
01:30:20,695 --> 01:30:24,265
<i>♪ To set us all free ♪</i>

1310
01:30:26,702 --> 01:30:28,103
I will take you there myself, personally.

1311
01:30:28,203 --> 01:30:31,673
<i>♪ Mother's devotion ♪</i>

1312
01:30:31,773 --> 01:30:35,276
<i>♪ To set us all free ♪</i>

1313
01:30:36,812 --> 01:30:39,414
CONGREGATION: <i>* For thee
For, for thee ♪</i>

1314
01:30:39,515 --> 01:30:42,718
<i>♪ Mother's devotion ♪</i>

1315
01:30:42,818 --> 01:30:46,788
<i>♪ To set us all free ♪</i>

1316
01:30:48,156 --> 01:30:50,526
CONGREGATION: <i>* For thee
For, for thee ♪</i>

1317
01:30:50,626 --> 01:30:54,129
ALL: <i>* Mother's devotion ♪</i>

1318
01:30:54,230 --> 01:30:57,733
<i>♪ To set us all free ♪</i>

1319
01:30:59,268 --> 01:31:02,171
CONGREGATION: <i>* For thee
For, for thee ♪</i>

1320
01:31:09,478 --> 01:31:13,249
(SCREAMING)

1321
01:31:13,349 --> 01:31:14,951
(THUMPING)

1322
01:31:20,089 --> 01:31:22,491
(PEOPLE VOCALIZING)

1323
01:31:24,160 --> 01:31:26,495
MARY (VO): <i>The first winter
proved most trying.</i>

1324
01:31:26,996 --> 01:31:28,898
<i>As they broke the land,</i>

1325
01:31:28,998 --> 01:31:32,502
<i>the swamp yielded its serpents
and stinging pests.</i>

1326
01:31:32,602 --> 01:31:34,504
(SINGING, HUMMING)

1327
01:31:34,604 --> 01:31:35,838
MARY (VO):
<i>Soon, sickness spread.</i>

1328
01:31:35,938 --> 01:31:36,906
(COUGHING)

1329
01:31:37,006 --> 01:31:38,207
MARY (VO):
<i>And fever took hold.</i>

1330
01:31:38,307 --> 01:31:41,778
(VOCALIZING CONTINUES)

1331
01:31:41,878 --> 01:31:44,281
MARY (VO): <i>The Shakers kept
friendly with their neighbors,</i>

1332
01:31:44,381 --> 01:31:46,983
<i>knowing them to be skilled
in woodworking,</i>

1333
01:31:47,083 --> 01:31:49,686
<i>and willing to trade
teaching for goods.</i>

1334
01:31:51,954 --> 01:31:55,458
- (CLAPPING)
- (VOCALIZING)

1335
01:31:56,726 --> 01:31:58,095
MARY (VO): <i>"Do all your work</i>

1336
01:31:58,195 --> 01:32:00,930
<i>as though you had
a thousand years to live</i>

1337
01:32:01,031 --> 01:32:04,167
<i>and as you would if you knew
you must die tomorrow,"</i>

1338
01:32:04,267 --> 01:32:06,336
<i>- she would say.</i>
- (ANN SCREAMING)

1339
01:32:09,372 --> 01:32:11,208
(PEOPLE HUMMING, SINGING)

1340
01:32:12,309 --> 01:32:14,211
MARY (VO):
<i>Like all true leaders,</i>

1341
01:32:14,311 --> 01:32:16,013
<i>Mother Ann
never asked her people</i>

1342
01:32:16,113 --> 01:32:17,948
<i>to do anything
she would not do herself.</i>

1343
01:32:18,048 --> 01:32:21,752
(VOCALIZING)

1344
01:32:21,852 --> 01:32:25,088
MARY (VO): <i>The Shakers knew
that the best way to reach God</i>

1345
01:32:25,188 --> 01:32:29,359
<i>was by laboring tirelessly,
always striving for perfection.</i>

1346
01:32:30,728 --> 01:32:32,596
<i>With indefatigable faith,</i>

1347
01:32:32,696 --> 01:32:36,199
<i>they toiled side-by-side
to raise a lasting home.</i>

1348
01:32:37,901 --> 01:32:40,938
<i>Little mindful of the war
that raged about them.</i>

1349
01:32:41,038 --> 01:32:44,207
(VOCALIZING CONTINUES)

1350
01:32:46,644 --> 01:32:48,179
MARY (VO): <i>At last,
she had found</i>

1351
01:32:48,279 --> 01:32:50,414
<i>a sanctuary for her people.</i>

1352
01:33:03,827 --> 01:33:05,897
For those new here,

1353
01:33:05,997 --> 01:33:09,133
who are unaccustomed
to a woman preacher.

1354
01:33:09,233 --> 01:33:11,803
WILLIAM:
"A woman shall compass a man."

1355
01:33:12,570 --> 01:33:16,307
Christ's spirit
first appeared as a man,

1356
01:33:16,407 --> 01:33:19,443
but has reappeared
to fulfill the promise

1357
01:33:19,543 --> 01:33:22,714
of the Second Coming as a woman.

1358
01:33:22,814 --> 01:33:24,448
Our Mother Ann.

1359
01:33:24,549 --> 01:33:28,487
And as we were all created
in His likeness, see,

1360
01:33:28,587 --> 01:33:33,692
God must be
both male and female.

1361
01:33:33,792 --> 01:33:36,027
For those wedded cohabitants
here today,

1362
01:33:37,296 --> 01:33:40,198
you must forsake
the marriage of the flesh

1363
01:33:40,299 --> 01:33:43,067
or you cannot
be married to the lamb.

1364
01:33:43,168 --> 01:33:45,504
We have had
the power of God upon us

1365
01:33:45,604 --> 01:33:48,273
and have felt great tribulation
for our sins.

1366
01:33:48,373 --> 01:33:52,177
After which we have felt
great love and releasement,

1367
01:33:52,277 --> 01:33:54,379
thought ourselves converted.

1368
01:33:54,980 --> 01:33:56,815
Is not this of Jesus Christ?

1369
01:33:56,915 --> 01:33:59,784
Yes, it is my brother
and husband.

1370
01:33:59,885 --> 01:34:01,520
It is us both, you see.

1371
01:34:02,587 --> 01:34:05,224
The gifts and calling of God

1372
01:34:05,324 --> 01:34:07,793
given to souls
in nature's darkness

1373
01:34:07,893 --> 01:34:10,262
not because they have repented,

1374
01:34:10,362 --> 01:34:14,066
but they are intended
to lead souls to repentance.

1375
01:34:15,034 --> 01:34:17,002
What is this repentance?

1376
01:34:17,102 --> 01:34:18,804
To leave off committing sin

1377
01:34:18,904 --> 01:34:21,173
is the only repentance
which God accepts.

1378
01:34:21,273 --> 01:34:25,210
Short of making an honest
and faithful confession

1379
01:34:25,310 --> 01:34:28,381
of all the sins ever committed
in your whole life.

1380
01:34:30,816 --> 01:34:34,219
It is God alone
that can forgive sins,

1381
01:34:34,320 --> 01:34:37,590
where then is the necessity
of confessing them to man?

1382
01:34:37,690 --> 01:34:39,925
WILLIAM: God has established
that order for all souls

1383
01:34:40,025 --> 01:34:43,229
who have committed sins that
they must confess their sins

1384
01:34:43,329 --> 01:34:45,565
before His chosen witnesses.

1385
01:34:47,167 --> 01:34:50,436
Do not be frightened, girl.
We do not bite.

1386
01:34:53,673 --> 01:34:55,808
Brother William tells me
you have borne seven children

1387
01:34:55,909 --> 01:34:57,510
yet at such a young age.

1388
01:34:58,711 --> 01:34:59,712
I have.

1389
01:35:02,115 --> 01:35:03,884
And did you receive them all
with equal joy?

1390
01:35:09,022 --> 01:35:09,856
(CLEARS THROAT)

1391
01:35:10,323 --> 01:35:11,124
No.

1392
01:35:12,959 --> 01:35:13,994
Is that so?

1393
01:35:17,063 --> 01:35:19,466
For she who confesses,
shams are over

1394
01:35:19,566 --> 01:35:21,334
and realities have begun.

1395
01:35:22,569 --> 01:35:24,705
She has exteriorized
her rottenness.

1396
01:35:29,410 --> 01:35:33,146
Routinely, see, when I went out
to fetch some water...

1397
01:35:34,915 --> 01:35:36,883
a terrible thought
might come on.

1398
01:35:38,051 --> 01:35:40,020
As I cradled our infant boy...

1399
01:35:42,789 --> 01:35:45,859
an overwhelming impulse
surged through me.

1400
01:35:47,594 --> 01:35:49,196
The desire to release him

1401
01:35:49,296 --> 01:35:51,232
into the depths of the well
and leave.

1402
01:35:54,368 --> 01:35:56,170
Seeking solace
from the undoubtedly

1403
01:35:56,270 --> 01:35:58,072
ceaseless wailing in the woods

1404
01:35:58,172 --> 01:35:59,440
behind the wash shed.

1405
01:36:03,077 --> 01:36:07,682
In that moment, the longing
for tranquility and silence

1406
01:36:07,782 --> 01:36:10,317
felt stronger
than the will to live.

1407
01:36:10,417 --> 01:36:12,386
- Give your grief to God.
- Give your grief to God.

1408
01:36:12,486 --> 01:36:14,489
- MAN: Your grief to God.
- Give your grief to God.

1409
01:36:14,589 --> 01:36:15,857
HOCKNELL:
Give your grief to God.

1410
01:36:15,957 --> 01:36:17,992
ANN: Give your grief to God.

1411
01:36:18,092 --> 01:36:20,094
Give your grief to God.

1412
01:36:20,194 --> 01:36:22,096
(WOMAN WAILING, SINGING)

1413
01:36:22,196 --> 01:36:24,065
(RHYTHMIC BREATHING)

1414
01:36:29,070 --> 01:36:31,306
(WAILING)

1415
01:36:31,406 --> 01:36:33,275
(MOANS)

1416
01:36:33,375 --> 01:36:36,043
(RHYTHMIC GRUNTING, BREATHING)

1417
01:36:38,380 --> 01:36:41,116
(ANN SHOUTS)

1418
01:36:41,216 --> 01:36:42,884
ANN: More love, Brothers!

1419
01:36:42,985 --> 01:36:44,386
(ALL GRUNTING)

1420
01:36:44,486 --> 01:36:46,454
More love, Sisters!

1421
01:36:47,855 --> 01:36:51,426
- (GRUNTING)
- (WOMEN WAILING)

1422
01:36:51,526 --> 01:36:53,761
This is our altar,

1423
01:36:54,863 --> 01:36:57,665
and our altar is love!

1424
01:36:59,467 --> 01:37:03,571
None can build this altar
or sacrifice upon it

1425
01:37:03,672 --> 01:37:06,441
but the pure in heart,

1426
01:37:06,542 --> 01:37:08,677
and such are we!

1427
01:37:09,612 --> 01:37:12,715
We will sacrifice upon it!

1428
01:37:12,815 --> 01:37:16,919
- And we will love each other!
- (GRUNTING, WAILING CONTINUE)

1429
01:37:24,660 --> 01:37:26,262
(GRUNTING, WAILING)

1430
01:37:35,671 --> 01:37:37,806
MARY (VO): <i>The trumpet
of Mother's everlasting gospel</i>

1431
01:37:37,906 --> 01:37:39,342
<i>began to sound.</i>

1432
01:37:40,243 --> 01:37:43,279
<i>And many flocked to Niskayuna
from various quarters.</i>

1433
01:37:45,882 --> 01:37:49,385
<i>Thus, the long expectations
of Ann Lee's church</i>

1434
01:37:49,485 --> 01:37:50,920
<i>were fully realized.</i>

1435
01:38:14,911 --> 01:38:16,446
William, the Elder?

1436
01:38:17,213 --> 01:38:21,050
WILLIAM: Yes, Brother, it is I.
Have we made acquaintance?

1437
01:38:21,150 --> 01:38:24,754
- (INDISTINCT)
- (CHATTERING, LAUGHING)

1438
01:38:33,363 --> 01:38:35,365
This way, children.
Come with me.

1439
01:38:38,168 --> 01:38:39,403
HEADMASTER: Come along now.

1440
01:38:41,571 --> 01:38:42,706
A place for everything,

1441
01:38:42,806 --> 01:38:44,574
and everything
in its place, William.

1442
01:38:46,743 --> 01:38:48,846
WILLIAM:
There are so many children.

1443
01:38:48,946 --> 01:38:52,482
We have found that
a great many need caring for

1444
01:38:52,582 --> 01:38:54,351
and plenty who have none.

1445
01:38:54,451 --> 01:38:56,386
Some come
with their mothers alone,

1446
01:38:56,486 --> 01:38:57,955
some come
with their fathers as well.

1447
01:38:59,423 --> 01:39:02,392
All little ones are free of sin.

1448
01:39:02,493 --> 01:39:05,596
Later, they can choose for
themselves to stay pure or not.

1449
01:39:08,365 --> 01:39:11,802
So, tell us, Brother.

1450
01:39:11,902 --> 01:39:13,904
You have
our undivided attention.

1451
01:39:15,205 --> 01:39:16,574
(SIGHS)

1452
01:39:17,608 --> 01:39:19,810
The devil is a real being.

1453
01:39:19,910 --> 01:39:21,946
As real as a bear.

1454
01:39:22,680 --> 01:39:25,283
And I know, for I have seen him
and fought with him.

1455
01:39:25,950 --> 01:39:27,318
But I have encountered
and gathered

1456
01:39:27,418 --> 01:39:29,254
a many righteous
brother and sister also.

1457
01:39:30,955 --> 01:39:33,458
I have amassed a following
across towns near and far.

1458
01:39:34,592 --> 01:39:35,994
A community of persons who long

1459
01:39:36,094 --> 01:39:38,263
to be in the presence
of their Mother Ann.

1460
01:39:38,363 --> 01:39:42,733
ANN: We have made a great
advancement during your absence.

1461
01:39:42,834 --> 01:39:43,969
WILLIAM: That, I can see.

1462
01:39:45,670 --> 01:39:48,306
Imagine my delight
at this land tilled,

1463
01:39:48,406 --> 01:39:51,442
edifice erected, new faces
in every and all direction.

1464
01:39:53,111 --> 01:39:55,046
It is exactly
as you said it would be.

1465
01:39:57,549 --> 01:40:00,719
Mother, I've seen a vision.

1466
01:40:03,489 --> 01:40:06,625
A large, black cloud rising
as black as thunder.

1467
01:40:07,659 --> 01:40:09,160
A wartime is coming.

1468
01:40:10,429 --> 01:40:11,630
You are not wrong.

1469
01:40:14,132 --> 01:40:15,801
WILLIAM: On my travels,
I obtained a pamphlet

1470
01:40:15,901 --> 01:40:19,271
from a Mr. Valentine Rathbun,
Minister of the Gospel

1471
01:40:19,371 --> 01:40:20,572
which concerns me greatly.

1472
01:40:20,672 --> 01:40:23,975
- May I read from it, Mother?
- You may.

1473
01:40:24,076 --> 01:40:27,146
"To obtain instruction from
the woman preacher, Ann Lee,

1474
01:40:27,246 --> 01:40:30,716
I went to Niskayuna and gave her
a lengthy relation of my life.

1475
01:40:31,417 --> 01:40:33,819
In return, she made me
many wonderful promises.

1476
01:40:35,254 --> 01:40:37,824
Shakerism
is a religion of bluff,

1477
01:40:37,924 --> 01:40:39,992
and its adherents are fanatics.

1478
01:40:40,092 --> 01:40:41,761
I myself beheld the following,

1479
01:40:41,861 --> 01:40:43,529
and know, therefore,
whereof I speak.

1480
01:40:43,629 --> 01:40:45,164
They meet together
in the dead of night

1481
01:40:45,264 --> 01:40:47,700
and have been heard
two miles away by people.

1482
01:40:47,800 --> 01:40:49,769
They run about in the woods
and elsewhere,

1483
01:40:49,869 --> 01:40:52,471
hooting and tooting like owls
while some dance

1484
01:40:52,572 --> 01:40:55,542
and make such a bedlam as only
the insane can thrive upon."

1485
01:40:55,642 --> 01:40:58,745
Yes, he was here for the winter,

1486
01:40:58,845 --> 01:41:01,147
but he was not well-suited
for our community

1487
01:41:01,247 --> 01:41:02,715
and was asked to leave.

1488
01:41:04,283 --> 01:41:07,620
Brother William,
this is to be expected.

1489
01:41:07,720 --> 01:41:10,857
For we have long endured
such slanderous conceits.

1490
01:41:10,957 --> 01:41:12,625
This is different.
It goes on and on.

1491
01:41:12,725 --> 01:41:14,126
But hear this.

1492
01:41:14,661 --> 01:41:16,729
"Most of those who join
Ann Lee's movement

1493
01:41:16,829 --> 01:41:18,165
are urged to cry out against

1494
01:41:18,265 --> 01:41:20,167
the military defense
of the country,

1495
01:41:20,267 --> 01:41:22,602
against fighting
the common British foe.

1496
01:41:23,136 --> 01:41:26,573
Ann Lee's scheming religion
is not only treasonous,

1497
01:41:27,307 --> 01:41:29,576
it is also aimed at bre--
(GRUNTS)

1498
01:41:29,676 --> 01:41:32,179
It is also aimed at breaking up
life as we know it.

1499
01:41:32,279 --> 01:41:35,415
She causes
husbands and wives to part.

1500
01:41:35,515 --> 01:41:38,418
I am convinced the spirit which
prevails over this new scheme

1501
01:41:38,518 --> 01:41:40,821
is the spirit of witchcraft.

1502
01:41:41,755 --> 01:41:45,726
Ann Lee is Satan in the guise
of a sweet angel of light.

1503
01:41:46,393 --> 01:41:48,896
Some of the women Shakers
strip naked in the woods."

1504
01:41:48,996 --> 01:41:51,665
MARY: That is because the
brethren pulled off their coats

1505
01:41:51,765 --> 01:41:53,501
or outside garments, to labor,

1506
01:41:53,601 --> 01:41:56,036
or as the world
would call it "dance."

1507
01:41:56,136 --> 01:41:59,740
And in warm weather the sisters
being lightly clothed, but...

1508
01:41:59,840 --> 01:42:02,410
but they would report
we dance naked!

1509
01:42:02,510 --> 01:42:04,312
And you know how apt

1510
01:42:04,412 --> 01:42:06,514
the ignorant and vulgar parts
of mankind are

1511
01:42:06,614 --> 01:42:08,349
to misrepresent
what they see.

1512
01:42:08,449 --> 01:42:11,619
If one told we dance naked
with but few clothes on,

1513
01:42:11,719 --> 01:42:13,521
another in telling the story
would miss out that part.

1514
01:42:13,621 --> 01:42:16,290
It is not the baseless
accusation of vulgarities

1515
01:42:16,390 --> 01:42:18,492
which concerns me, Sister Mary.

1516
01:42:18,592 --> 01:42:21,229
For treason,
Mother could be jailed or worse.

1517
01:42:21,329 --> 01:42:24,065
ANN: Not long ago,
a general came along

1518
01:42:24,165 --> 01:42:25,766
with two magisterial gentlemen
on horseback,

1519
01:42:25,867 --> 01:42:27,501
declaring that they required

1520
01:42:27,601 --> 01:42:30,038
we take an oath of allegiance
to the country

1521
01:42:30,872 --> 01:42:33,742
and join them in the fight
for this nation's independence.

1522
01:42:36,077 --> 01:42:38,647
And what did you reply?

1523
01:42:38,747 --> 01:42:41,449
I merely explained that
the people of this community

1524
01:42:41,549 --> 01:42:43,017
will never do them any hurt,

1525
01:42:43,117 --> 01:42:44,919
for we are well-wishers
to the country.

1526
01:42:45,019 --> 01:42:46,788
And we will do all the good
to the country

1527
01:42:46,888 --> 01:42:48,222
that we are able to do.

1528
01:42:49,558 --> 01:42:50,425
Good.

1529
01:42:52,461 --> 01:42:53,361
That is good.

1530
01:42:55,930 --> 01:42:59,167
But I also made explicit
that we are unwilling

1531
01:42:59,268 --> 01:43:02,471
and unable to kill the devil
with the sword.

1532
01:43:02,971 --> 01:43:04,406
Hear me.
We must hide you, Mother.

1533
01:43:04,506 --> 01:43:07,709
William, sit down.
Do not be rash. Rest, please.

1534
01:43:07,809 --> 01:43:09,611
I need you to hear me.
They will return for you.

1535
01:43:09,711 --> 01:43:11,746
Rest, William.

1536
01:43:11,846 --> 01:43:14,849
All will be clear as
crystal glass on the morrow.

1537
01:44:13,743 --> 01:44:17,247
(PATSY HUMMING)

1538
