<i>♪ I love her way ♪</i>

1607
01:49:19,054 --> 01:49:23,391
(HOOFSTEPS RUMBLING FAINTLY)

1608
01:49:24,460 --> 01:49:27,596
MARY (VO): <i>A month later,
Mother Ann was taken away</i>

1609
01:49:28,330 --> 01:49:30,566
<i>just as Brother William
had predicted.</i>

1610
01:50:06,335 --> 01:50:09,338
<i>The Elder, James Whittaker,
traveled at once</i>

1611
01:50:09,438 --> 01:50:11,173
<i>to inform the Governor
of New York</i>

1612
01:50:11,273 --> 01:50:13,375
<i>about Mother Ann's
imprisonment, harsh treatment</i>

1613
01:50:13,475 --> 01:50:14,944
<i>and sufferings.</i>

1614
01:50:15,044 --> 01:50:16,312
(BELL TOLLING)

1615
01:50:16,412 --> 01:50:18,615
<i>The Governor, George Clinton,</i>

1616
01:50:18,715 --> 01:50:21,083
<i>pronounced disapproval
of jailing persons</i>

1617
01:50:21,183 --> 01:50:23,052
<i>for their pious beliefs.</i>

1618
01:50:23,586 --> 01:50:26,589
<i>And due to lack
of treasonable evidence,</i>

1619
01:50:26,689 --> 01:50:28,791
<i>he believed the woman
should be freed.</i>

1620
01:50:28,891 --> 01:50:30,927
(BELL TOLLING)

1621
01:50:31,027 --> 01:50:32,262
(BIRDS CAWING)

1622
01:50:47,945 --> 01:50:49,880
(JOHN COUGHING)

1623
01:50:50,247 --> 01:50:51,314
Mother.

1624
01:50:52,349 --> 01:50:53,316
Mother.

1625
01:50:56,386 --> 01:50:57,554
Rest, Brother.

1626
01:50:58,221 --> 01:51:01,291
(JOHN MOANING)

1627
01:51:01,391 --> 01:51:03,126
We've travelled day and night,
Brother Hocknell.

1628
01:51:03,226 --> 01:51:04,361
Mother is here now.

1629
01:51:05,629 --> 01:51:08,165
He's taken no food
for the last day.

1630
01:51:08,265 --> 01:51:11,802
We came as fast as we were able.
Rest, brother.

1631
01:51:11,902 --> 01:51:13,671
(JOHN GROANS)

1632
01:51:16,039 --> 01:51:19,209
(SIGHS) Last--

1633
01:51:19,309 --> 01:51:25,916
Last month, God's gift
cured me whooping cough,

1634
01:51:26,517 --> 01:51:31,155
but it remanifested as
these blisters on my hands

1635
01:51:31,922 --> 01:51:36,427
to signal that my work
here was not yet done.

1636
01:51:37,228 --> 01:51:42,366
He spoke to me and said,
"I have work for you to do,

1637
01:51:42,466 --> 01:51:45,169
and when your--
your work is done...

1638
01:51:46,837 --> 01:51:51,342
the same cough
will return to you

1639
01:51:52,777 --> 01:51:55,113
and take you out of this world."

1640
01:51:57,015 --> 01:52:01,720
So, we labored to finish the
second dwelling house, Mother.

1641
01:52:03,154 --> 01:52:05,523
The house is beautiful,
Brother John.

1642
01:52:06,891 --> 01:52:08,760
(BELL TOLLING)

1643
01:52:15,900 --> 01:52:17,769
(BELL TOLLING CONTINUES)

1644
01:52:28,447 --> 01:52:30,382
MARY (VO): <i>Having again</i>

1645
01:52:30,482 --> 01:52:32,784
<i>lost six precious months
of her lifetime</i>

1646
01:52:32,884 --> 01:52:35,087
<i>to a term of incarceration,</i>

1647
01:52:35,187 --> 01:52:38,457
<i>she soon set forth
on a spiritual crusade</i>

1648
01:52:38,557 --> 01:52:41,093
<i>to spread the Gospel
throughout New England.</i>

1649
01:52:41,193 --> 01:52:47,900
<i>♪ How can I but love
My dear faithful children ♪</i>

1650
01:52:51,804 --> 01:52:57,209
<i>♪ Who are willing to bear
And suffer with me ♪</i>

1651
01:52:59,645 --> 01:53:05,217
<i>♪ When I was on earth
And in a cold prison ♪</i>

1652
01:53:05,751 --> 01:53:09,755
MARY (VO): <i>A two-year journey
traveling hundreds of miles,</i>

1653
01:53:09,855 --> 01:53:12,858
<i>suffering indescribable
hardships and persecution.</i>

1654
01:53:15,461 --> 01:53:18,964
<i>♪ I cried to my God ♪</i>

1655
01:53:19,064 --> 01:53:22,835
<i>♪ To remember poor me ♪</i>

1656
01:53:25,070 --> 01:53:27,940
(ANN GASPING PERCUSSIVELY)

1657
01:53:38,184 --> 01:53:40,987
(HORSES WHINNY, NEIGH)

1658
01:53:48,361 --> 01:53:50,463
MAN: Whoa! Whoa!

1659
01:53:50,563 --> 01:53:52,098
(HORSE WHINNIES)

1660
01:53:52,198 --> 01:53:54,334
JAMES: Ye watched, for ye knew
not which hour we would come.

1661
01:53:54,434 --> 01:53:58,404
ANN: It is good to watch.
It is always good to watch.

1662
01:53:58,504 --> 01:54:01,508
SHATTUCK: Welcome, Mother.
It is an honor to host you.

1663
01:54:01,608 --> 01:54:03,376
I think you
will be delighted to see

1664
01:54:03,477 --> 01:54:05,846
how many have accepted
our invitation this night.

1665
01:54:05,946 --> 01:54:07,881
(FAINT SINGING)

1666
01:54:09,750 --> 01:54:11,217
(HORSES WHINNY)

1667
01:54:16,923 --> 01:54:18,792
(CONGREGATION WAILING)

1668
01:54:21,695 --> 01:54:24,598
(WAILING)

1669
01:54:35,009 --> 01:54:38,179
